quran[1606]{c,v,t}:
  50,1,Qaf. By the Glorious Qur'an
  50,2,"Nay, they wonder that there has come to them a warner from among themselves. So the disbelievers say: \"This is a strange thing"
  50,3,When we are dead and have become dust. (Shall we be resurrected) That is a far return
  50,4,"We know that which the earth takes of them, and with Us is a Book preserved"
  50,5,"Nay, but they have denied the truth when it has come to them, so they are in a Marij state"
  50,6,"Have they not looked at the heaven above them, how We have made it and adorned it, and there are no Furuj in it"
  50,7,"And the earth! We have spread it out, and set thereon Rawasi standing firm, and We planted in it every lovely (Bahij) pair"
  50,8,An insight and a Reminder for every servant who turns to Allah in repentance
  50,9,"And We send down blessed water (rain) from the sky, then We produce therewith Jannat and grain that are reaped"
  50,10,"And date palms Basiqat, with arranged clusters"
  50,11,A provision for the servants. And We give life therewith to a dead land. Thus will be the Resurrection
  50,12,"Denied before them the people of Nuh, and the Dwellers of Rass, and Thamud"
  50,13,"And `Ad, and Fir`awn, and the brethren of Lut"
  50,14,"And the Dwellers of Al-Aykah, and the people of Tubba`. Everyone of them denied (their) Messengers, so My threat took effect"
  50,15,"Were We then tired with the first creation Nay, they are in confused doubt about a new creation"
  50,16,"And indeed We have created man, and We know what his self whispers to him. And We are nearer to him than his jugular vein"
  50,17,"(Remember) that the two receivers (recording angels) receive (each human being), one sitting on the right and one on the left"
  50,18,Not a word does he (or she) utter but there is a watcher by him ready (to record it)
  50,19,"And the stupor of death will come in truth: \"This is what you have been avoiding"
  50,20,And the Trumpet will be blown -- that will be the Day of the threat
  50,21,And every person will come forth along with a Sa'iq and a Shahid
  50,22,"(It will be said to the sinners): \"Indeed you were heedless of this. Now We have removed from you, your covering, and sharp is your sight this Day"
  50,23,"And his companion (angel) will say: \"Here is (his record) ready with me"
  50,24,"(Allah will say to the angels:) \"Both of you throw into Hell every stubborn disbeliever"
  50,25,"Hinderer of good, transgressor, doubter"
  50,26,Who set up another god with Allah. Then both of you cast him in the severe torment
  50,27,"His companion (devil) will say: \"Our Lord! I did not push him to transgression, but he was himself in error far astray"
  50,28,"(Allah) will say: \"Dispute not in front of Me, I had already in advance sent you the threat"
  50,29,"The sentence that comes from Me cannot be changed, and I am not unjust to the servants"
  50,30,"On the Day when We will say to Hell: \"Are you filled\" It will say: \"Are there any more"
  50,31,"And Paradise will be Uzlifat to those who had Taqwa, not far off"
  50,32,"(It will be said): \"This is what you were promised -- (it is) for those returning in sincere repentance, and Hafiz"
  50,33,Who feared Ar-Rahman unseen and brought a heart turned in repentance
  50,34,Enter you therein in peace and security -- this is a Day of eternal life
  50,35,There they will have all that they desire -- and We have more
  50,36,And how many a generation We have destroyed before them who were stronger in power than they. And they went about the land! Could they find any place of refuge
  50,37,"Verily, therein is indeed a reminder for him who has a heart or gives ear while he is heedful"
  50,38,And indeed We created the heavens and the earth and all between them in six Days and nothing of fatigue touched Us
  50,39,"So bear with patience all that they say, and glorify the praises of your Lord, before the rising of the sun and before (its) setting"
  50,40,And during a part of the night (also) glorify His praises and (so likewise) after the prostrations
  50,41,And listen on the Day when the caller will call from a near place
  50,42,"The Day when they will hear As-Sayhah in truth, that will be the Day of coming out"
  50,43,"Verily, it is We Who give life and cause death; and to Us is the final return"
  50,44,"On the Day when the earth shall be cleft, from off them (they will come out) hastening forth. That will be a gathering, quite easy for Us"
  50,45,We know best what they say. And you are not the one to force them. But warn by the Qur'an; him who fears My threat
  51,1,By the scattering Dhariyat
  51,2,And the laden Hamilat
  51,3,And the steady Jariyat
  51,4,And the distributors of command
  51,5,"Verily, that which you are promised is surely true"
  51,6,"And verily, Ad-Din is sure to occur"
  51,7,By the heaven full of Hubuk
  51,8,"Certainly, you have different ideas"
  51,9,Turned aside therefrom is he who is turned aside
  51,10,Cursed be Al-Kharrasun
  51,11,Who are under a cover of Sahun
  51,12,"They ask: \"When will be the Day of Ad-Din"
  51,13,(It will be) a Day when they will be Yuftanun in the Fire
  51,14,Taste you your trial! This is what you used to ask to be hastened
  51,15,"Verily, those who have Taqwa will be in the midst of Gardens and Springs"
  51,16,"Taking joy in the things which their Lord has given them. Verily, they were before this doers of good"
  51,17,They used to sleep but little by night
  51,18,"And in the hours before dawn, they were asking for forgiveness"
  51,19,And in their wealth there was the right of the Sa'il and the Mahrum
  51,20,And on the earth are signs for those who have faith with certainty
  51,21,And also in yourselves. Will you not then see
  51,22,"And in the heaven is your provision, and that which you are promised"
  51,23,"Then by the Lord of the heaven and the earth, it is the truth, just as you can speak"
  51,24,"Has the story reached you, of the honored guests of Ibrahim"
  51,25,"When they came in to him and said: \"Salaman!\" He answered: \"Salamun\" and said: \"You are a people unknown to me"
  51,26,"Then he turned to his household, and brought out a roasted calf"
  51,27,"And placed it before them (saying): \"Will you not eat"
  51,28,"Then he conceived fear of them (when they ate not). They said: \"Fear not.\" And they gave him glad tidings of a son having knowledge"
  51,29,"Then his wife came forward with a loud voice; she smote her face, and said: \"A barren old woman"
  51,30,"They said: \"Even so says your Lord. Verily, He is the All-Wise, the All-Knower"
  51,31,"(Ibrahim) said: \"Then for what purpose you have come, O messengers"
  51,32,"They said: \"We have been sent to a people who are criminals"
  51,33,To send down upon them stones of clay
  51,34,Marked by your Lord for transgressors
  51,35,So We brought out from therein the believers
  51,36,But We found not there any household of the Muslims except one
  51,37,And We have left there a sign for those who fear the painful torment
  51,38,"And in Musa, when We sent him to Fir`awn with a manifest authority"
  51,39,"But (he) turned away along with his hosts, and said: \"A sorcerer or a madman"
  51,40,"So We took him and his armies, and dumped them into the sea (Yamm), for he was blameworthy"
  51,41,And in `Ad when We sent against them the barren wind
  51,42,"It spared nothing that it reached, but blew it into broken spreads of rotten ruins"
  51,43,"And in Thamud, when they were told: \"Enjoy yourselves for a while"
  51,44,"But they insolently defied the command of their Lord, so the Sa`iqah overtook them while they were looking"
  51,45,"Then they were unable to rise up, nor could they help themselves"
  51,46,"(So were) the people of Nuh before them. Verily, they were a people who were rebellious"
  51,47,"With Hands We constructed the heaven. Verily, We are able to expand the vastness of space thereof"
  51,48,And We have made the earth a Firash; how excellent spreader (thereof) are We
  51,49,"And of everything We have created pairs, that you may remember"
  51,50,"So, flee to Allah. Verily, I am a plain warner to you from Him"
  51,51,"And set not up any other god along with Allah. Verily, I am a plain warner to you from Him"
  51,52,"Likewise, no Messenger came to those before them but they said: \"A sorcerer or a madman"
  51,53,"Have they transmitted this saying to these Nay, they are themselves a people transgressing beyond bounds"
  51,54,"So turn away from them, you are not blameworthy"
  51,55,"And remind, for verily, the reminding profits the believers"
  51,56,And I created not the Jinn and mankind except that they should worship Me
  51,57,I seek not any provision from them nor do I ask that they should feed Me
  51,58,"Verily, Allah is the All-Provider, Owner of power, the Most Strong"
  51,59,"And verily, for those who do wrong, there is a portion of torment like to the evil portion of torment (which came for) their likes (of old); so let them not ask Me to hasten on"
  51,60,Then woe to those who disbelieve from their Day which they have been promised
  52,1,By the Tur
  52,2,And the Book inscribed
  52,3,In parchment unrolled
  52,4,And by Al-Bayt Al-Ma`mur
  52,5,And the roof raised high
  52,6,And by the sea that is Masjur
  52,7,"Verily, the torment of your Lord will surely come to pass"
  52,8,There is none that can avert it
  52,9,On the Day when Tamur the heaven Mawr
  52,10,And Tasir the mountains Sayr
  52,11,Then woe that Day to those who denied
  52,12,"Those who were, in their falsehood, playing"
  52,13,"The Day when they will be pushed down by force to the fire of Hell, with a horrible, forceful pushing"
  52,14,This is the Fire which you used to deny
  52,15,Is this magic or do you not see
  52,16,"Enter therein and whether you are patient of it or impatient of it, it is all the same. You are only being requited for what you used to do"
  52,17,"Verily, those who have Taqwa will be in Gardens and Delight"
  52,18,"Enjoying in that which their Lord has bestowed on them, and (the fact that) their Lord saved them from the torment of the blazing Fire"
  52,19,Eat and drink with happiness because of what you used to do
  52,20,They will recline on thrones Masfufah. And We shall marry them to Hur (fair females) with wide lovely eyes
  52,21,"And those who believe and whose offspring follow them in faith, -- to them shall We join their offspring, and We shall not decrease the reward of their deeds in anything. Every person is a pledge for that which he has earned"
  52,22,And We shall provide them with fruit and meat such as they desire
  52,23,"There they shall pass from hand to hand a cup, free from any idle talk, and free from sin"
  52,24,"And there will go round boy-servants of theirs, to serve them as if they were preserved pearls"
  52,25,"And some of them draw near to others, questioning"
  52,26,"Saying: \"Aforetime, we were afraid in the midst of our families"
  52,27,"So Allah has been gracious to us, and has saved us from the torment of the Fire"
  52,28,"Verily, We used to invoke Him before. Verily, He is the Most Subtle, the Most Merciful"
  52,29,"Therefore, remind. By the grace of Allah, you are neither a Kahin nor a madman"
  52,30,"Or do they say: \"A poet! We await for him some calamity by time"
  52,31,"Say: \"Wait! I am with you among those who wait"
  52,32,Or do their minds command them this or are they people transgressing all bounds
  52,33,"Or do they say: \"He has forged it\" Nay! They believe not"
  52,34,Let them then produce a recitation like unto it if they are truthful
  52,35,Or were they created by nothing Or were they themselves the creators
  52,36,"Or did they create the heavens and the earth Nay, but they have no firm belief"
  52,37,Or are with them the treasures of your Lord Or are they the tyrants with the authority to do as they like
  52,38,"Or have they a stairway (to heaven), by means of which they listen Then let their listener produce some manifest proof"
  52,39,Or has He only daughters and you have sons
  52,40,Or is it that you ask a wage from them so that they are burdened with a load of debt
  52,41,"Or that the Unseen is with them, and they write it down"
  52,42,Or do they intend a plot But those who disbelieve are themselves plotted against
  52,43,Or have they a god other than Allah Glorified be Allah from all that they ascribe as partners
  52,44,"And if they were to see a piece of the heaven falling down, they would say: \"Clouds gathered in heaps"
  52,45,"So leave them alone till they meet their Day, in which they will sink into a fainting (with horror)"
  52,46,"The Day when their plotting shall not avail them at all, nor will they be helped"
  52,47,"And verily, for those who do wrong, there is another punishment before this; but most of them know not"
  52,48,"So wait patiently for the decision of your Lord, for verily, you are under Our Eyes; and glorify the praises of your Lord when you get up"
  52,49,And in the nighttime also glorify His praises and at the setting of the stars
  53,1,By the star when it goes down
  53,2,Your companion has neither gone astray nor has he erred
  53,3,Nor does he speak of desire
  53,4,It is only a revelation revealed
  53,5,He has been taught by one mighty in power
  53,6,Dhu Mirrah then he Istawa
  53,7,While he was in the highest part of the horizon
  53,8,Then he approached and came closer
  53,9,And was at a distance of two bows' length or less
  53,10,So (Allah) revealed to His servant whatever He revealed
  53,11,The heart lied not in what he saw
  53,12,Will you then dispute with him about what he saw
  53,13,And indeed he saw him at a second descent
  53,14,Near Sidrat Al-Muntaha
  53,15,Near it is the Paradise of Abode
  53,16,When that covered the lote tree which did cover it
  53,17,"The sight turned not aside, nor it transgressed beyond the limit"
  53,18,Indeed he saw of the greatest Ssgns of his Lord
  53,19,"Have you then considered Al-Lat, and Al-`Uzza"
  53,20,"And Manat, the other third"
  53,21,Is it for you the males and for Him the females
  53,22,That indeed is a division most unfair
  53,23,"They are but names which you have named - you and your fathers - for which Allah has sent down no authority. They follow but a guess and that which they themselves desire, whereas there has surely come to them the guidance from their Lord"
  53,24,Or shall man have what he wishes
  53,25,But to Allah belongs the last (Hereafter) and the first (the world)
  53,26,"And there are many angels in the heavens, whose intercession will avail nothing, except after Allah has given leave for whom He wills and is pleased with"
  53,27,"Verily, those who believe not in the Hereafter, name the angels with female names"
  53,28,"But they have no knowledge thereof. They follow but conjecture, and verily, conjecture is no substitute for the truth"
  53,29,Therefore withdraw from him who turns away from Our Reminder and desires nothing but the life of this world
  53,30,"That is what they could reach of knowledge. Verily, your Lord is He, Who knows best him who goes astray from His path, and He knows best him who receives guidance"
  53,31,"And to Allah belongs all that is in the heavens and all that is on the earth, that He may requite those who do evil with that which they have done, and reward those who do good, with what is best"
  53,32,"Those who avoid great sins and Al-Fawahish (immoral sins) except Al-Lamam -- verily, your Lord is of vast forgiveness. He knows you well when He created you from the earth (Adam), and when you were fetuses in your mothers' wombs. So, ascribe not purity to yourselves. He knows best him who has Taqwa"
  53,33,Did you observe him who turned away (from Islam)
  53,34,"And gave a little, then stopped"
  53,35,Is with him the knowledge of the Unseen so that he sees
  53,36,Or is he not informed with what is in the Suhuf of Musa
  53,37,And of Ibrahim who fulfilled all that
  53,38,That no burdened person (with sins) shall bear the burden (sins) of another
  53,39,And that man can have nothing but what he does
  53,40,And that his deeds will be seen
  53,41,Then he will be recompensed with a full and the best recompense
  53,42,And that to your Lord is the End
  53,43,"And that it is He Who makes laugh, and makes weep"
  53,44,And that it is He Who causes death and gives life
  53,45,"And that He creates the pairs, male and female"
  53,46,From Nutfah when it is emitted
  53,47,And that upon Him is another bringing forth (Resurrection)
  53,48,And that it is He Who Aghna and Aqna
  53,49,And that He is the Lord of Ash-Shi`ra
  53,50,And that it is He Who destroyed the former `Ad
  53,51,And Thamud. He spared none of them
  53,52,"And the people of Nuh aforetime. Verily, they were more unjust and more rebellious and transgressing"
  53,53,And He destroyed the overthrown cities
  53,54,"So, there covered them that which did cover"
  53,55,Then which of the graces of your Lord will you doubt
  53,56,This is a warner from the warners of old
  53,57,The Azifah draws near
  53,58,None besides Allah can avert it
  53,59,Do you then wonder at this reci- tation
  53,60,And you laugh at it and weep not
  53,61,While you are Samidun
  53,62,So fall you down in prostration to Allah and worship Him
  54,1,"The Hour has drawn near, and the moon has been cleft asunder"
  54,2,"And if they see an Ayah, they turn away and say: \"This is magic, Mustamir"
  54,3,They denied and followed their own lusts. And every matter will be settled
  54,4,And indeed there has come to them news wherein there is Muzdajar
  54,5,"Perfect wisdom, but warners benefit them not"
  54,6,So withdraw from them. The Day that the caller will call (them) to a terrible thing
  54,7,"They will come forth, with humbled eyes from (their) graves as if they were locusts spread abroad"
  54,8,"Hastening towards the caller. The disbelievers will say: \"This is a hard Day"
  54,9,"The people of Nuh denied (their Messenger) before them. They rejected Our servant and said: \"A madman!\" Wazdujir"
  54,10,"Then he invoked his Lord (saying): \"I have been overcome, so help (me)"
  54,11,"So, We opened the gates of the heaven with water Munhamir"
  54,12,"And We caused springs to gush forth from the earth. So, the waters met for a matter predestined"
  54,13,And We carried him on a (ship) made of planks and nails (Dusur)
  54,14,"Floating under Our Eyes, a reward for him who had been rejected"
  54,15,"And indeed, We have left this as a sign. Then is there any that will remember"
  54,16,Then how (terrible) was My torment and My warnings
  54,17,And We have indeed made the Qur'an easy to understand and remember; then is there anyone who will remember
  54,18,Ad denied; then how was My torment and My warnings
  54,19,"Verily, We sent against them a violently cold (Sarsar) wind on a day of calamity, continuous"
  54,20,Plucking out men as if they were uprooted stems of date palms
  54,21,"Then, how was My torment and My warnings"
  54,22,And We have indeed made the Qur'an easy to understand and remember; then is there any that will remember
  54,23,Thamud denied the warnings
  54,24,"And they said: \"A man, alone among us -- shall we follow him Truly, then we should be in error and distress"
  54,25,"Is it that the Reminder is sent to him alone from among us Nay, he is an insolent liar"
  54,26,"Tomorrow they will come to know who is the liar, the insolent one"
  54,27,"Verily, We are sending the she-camel as a test for them. So watch them, and be patient"
  54,28,"And inform them that the water is to be shared between (her and) them, each one's right to drink being established (by turns)"
  54,29,But they called their comrade and he took (a sword) and killed (her)
  54,30,"Then, how was My torment and My warnings"
  54,31,"Verily, We sent against them a single Sayhah, and they became like straw Al-Muhtazir"
  54,32,"And indeed, We have made the Qur'an easy to understand and remember; then is there any that will remember"
  54,33,The people of Lut denied the warnings
  54,34,"Verily, We sent against them Hasib (a violent storm of stones), except the family of Lut, them We saved in the last hour of the night"
  54,35,As a favor from Us. Thus do We reward him who gives thanks
  54,36,"And he indeed had warned them of Our punishment, but they doubted the warnings"
  54,37,"And they indeed sought to shame his guests. So, We blinded their eyes (saying), \"Then taste you My torment and My warnings"
  54,38,"And verily, an abiding torment seized them early in the morning"
  54,39,Then taste you My torment and My warnings
  54,40,"And indeed, We have made the Qur'an easy to understand and remember; then is there any that will remember"
  54,41,"And indeed, warnings came to the people of Fir`awn"
  54,42,"(They) denied all Our signs, so We seized them with a punishment of the Almighty, All-Capable"
  54,43,Are your disbelievers better than these Or have you immunity in the Divine Scriptures
  54,44,"Or say they: \"We are a great multitude, victorious"
  54,45,"Their multitude will be put to flight, and they will show their backs"
  54,46,"Nay, but the Hour is their appointed time, and the Hour will be more grievous and more bitter"
  54,47,"Verily, the criminals are in error and will burn"
  54,48,"The Day they will be dragged on their faces into the Fire (it will be said to them): \"Taste you the touch of Hell"
  54,49,"Verily, We have created all things with Qadar"
  54,50,And Our commandment is but one as the twinkling of an eye
  54,51,"And indeed, We have destroyed your likes; then is there any that will remember"
  54,52,And everything they have done is noted in Az-Zubur
  54,53,"And everything, small and large, is written down"
  54,54,"Verily, those who have Taqwa, will be in the midst of Gardens and Rivers"
  54,55,"In a seat of truth, near the Muqtadir King"
  55,1,Ar-Rahman
  55,2,He has taught the Qur'an
  55,3,He created man
  55,4,He taught him Al-Bayan
  55,5,The sun and the moon (run) on fixed courses
  55,6,And the Najm and the trees prostrating
  55,7,"And the heaven He has raised high, and He has set up the balance"
  55,8,In order that you may not transgress the balance
  55,9,And observe the weight with equity and do not make the balance deficient
  55,10,And the earth He has put down (laid) for Al-An'am
  55,11,"Therein are fruits, date palms producing Akmam"
  55,12,"And also corn, with (its) `Asf, and Rayhan"
  55,13,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,14,He created man from sounding clay like the clay of pottery
  55,15,And the Jinn He created from a smokeless flame of fire
  55,16,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,17,The Lord of the two easts and the Lord of the two wests
  55,18,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,19,He has Maraja the two seas meeting together
  55,20,Between them is a barrier which none of them can transgress
  55,21,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,22,Out of them both come out pearls and Al-Marjan
  55,23,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,24,"And His are Al-Jawar Al-Munsha'at, in the seas like A`lam"
  55,25,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,26,Whatsoever is on it (the earth) will perish
  55,27,And the Face of your Lord Dhul-Jalal wal-Ikram will remain forever
  55,28,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,29,Whosoever is in the heavens and on the earth begs of Him. Every day He is (engaged) in some affair
  55,30,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,31,"We shall attend to you, O Thaqalan"
  55,32,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,33,"O assembly of Jinn and men! If you are able to pass beyond the zones of the heavens and the earth, then pass beyond (them)! But you will never be able to pass them, except with authority (from Allah)"
  55,34,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,35,"There will be sent against you both, Shuwaz of fire and Nuhas, and you will not be able to defend yourselves"
  55,36,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,37,"Then when the heaven is rent asunder, and it becomes Wardah like Dihan"
  55,38,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,39,"So, on that Day he will not be questioned about his sin, (neither) human nor Jinn"
  55,40,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,41,"The criminals will be known by their marks, and they will be seized by their foreheads and feet"
  55,42,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,43,This is the Hell which the criminals denied
  55,44,They will go between it and Hamim An
  55,45,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,46,"But for him who fears the standing before his Lord, there will be two Gardens"
  55,47,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,48,With Afnan
  55,49,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,50,In them (both) will be two springs flowing (free)
  55,51,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,52,In them (both) will be every kind of fruit in pairs
  55,53,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,54,"Reclining upon the couches lined with Istabraq, and the fruits of the two Gardens will be near at hand"
  55,55,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,56,"Wherein both will be Qasirat At-Tarf, whom never deflowered a human before nor Jinn"
  55,57,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,58,They are like Yaqut and Marjan
  55,59,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,60,Is there any reward for good other than good
  55,61,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,62,"And below these two, there are two other Gardens"
  55,63,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,64,Mudhammatan
  55,65,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,66,In them (both) will be two springs Naddakhatan
  55,67,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,68,"In them (both) will be fruits, and date palms and pomegranates"
  55,69,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,70,Therein (Gardens) will be Khayrat Hisan
  55,71,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,72,"Hur (beautiful, fair females) guarded in pavilions"
  55,73,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,74,Whom never deflowered a human before nor Jinn
  55,75,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,76,Reclining on green Rafraf and rich beautiful `Abqariy
  55,77,Then which of the blessings of your Lord will you both deny
  55,78,"Blessed be the Name of your Lord, Dhil-Jalali wal-Ikram"
  56,1,When the Waqi`ah occurs
  56,2,"There is not, for its occurrence, Kadhibah"
  56,3,"Bringing low (some), exalting (others)"
  56,4,When the earth will be shaken with a terrible shake
  56,5,And the mountains will be powdered to dust
  56,6,So that they will become floating dust particles
  56,7,And you (all) will be in three groups
  56,8,So those on the right -- how (fortunate) will be those on the right
  56,9,And those on the left -- how (unfortunate) will be those on the left
  56,10,And those foremost will be foremost
  56,11,These will be the nearest (to Allah)
  56,12,In the Gardens of Delight
  56,13,A multitude of those will be from the first ones
  56,14,And a few of those will be from the later ones
  56,15,"(They will be) on thrones, Mawdunah"
  56,16,"Reclining thereon, face to face"
  56,17,Immortal boys will go around them (serving)
  56,18,"With cups, and jugs, and a glass of flowing wine"
  56,19,Wherefrom neither Yusadda`un nor Yunzifun
  56,20,And with fruit that they may choose
  56,21,And with the flesh of fowls that they desire
  56,22,And (there will be) Hur with wide lovely eyes
  56,23,Like preserved pearls
  56,24,A reward for what they used to do
  56,25,"No Laghw (evil vain talk) will they hear therein, nor any sinful speech"
  56,26,"But only the saying of: \"Salaman! Salaman"
  56,27,And those on the right -- how (fortunate) will be those on the right
  56,28,(They will be) among Sidri Makhdud
  56,29,And among Talh Mandud
  56,30,And in shade Mamdud
  56,31,And by water flowing constantly
  56,32,And fruit in plenty
  56,33,Whose supply is not cut off nor are they out of reach
  56,34,"And on couches, raised high"
  56,35,"Verily, We have created them a special creation"
  56,36,And made them virgins
  56,37,"Urub, Atrab"
  56,38,For those on the right
  56,39,A multitude of those will be from the first generation
  56,40,And a multitude of those will be from the later generations
  56,41,And those on the left How will be those on the left
  56,42,"In Samum, and Hamim"
  56,43,And a shadow from Yahmum
  56,44,Neither Barid nor Karim
  56,45,"Verily, before that, they indulged in luxury"
  56,46,And were persisting in great sin
  56,47,"And they used to say: \"When we die and become dust and bones, shall we then indeed be resurrected"
  56,48,And also our forefathers
  56,49,"Say: \"(Yes) verily, those of old, and those of later times"
  56,50,All will surely be gathered together for appointed meeting of a known Day
  56,51,"Then verily, --- you the erring -- ones, the deniers"
  56,52,"You verily, will eat of the trees of Zaqqum"
  56,53,Then you will fill your bellies therewith
  56,54,And drink the Hamim on top of it
  56,55,And you will drink (that) like Al-Him
  56,56,That will be their entertainment on the Day of Recompense
  56,57,"We created you, then why do you believe not"
  56,58,Do you not see the semen you emit
  56,59,"Is it you who create it, or are We the Creator"
  56,60,"We have decreed death to you all, and We are not outstripped"
  56,61,To transfigure you and create you in (forms) that you know not
  56,62,"And indeed, you have already known the first form of creation, why then do you not remember"
  56,63,Do you not see what you sow
  56,64,"Is it you that make it grow, or are We the Grower"
  56,65,"Were it Our will, We could crumble it to dry pieces, and you would be Tafakkahun"
  56,66,"(Saying:) \"We are indeed Mughramun"
  56,67,"Nay, but we are deprived"
  56,68,Do you not see the water that you drink
  56,69,"Is it you who cause it to come down from Al-Muzn, or are We the Cause of it coming down"
  56,70,"If We willed, We verily could make it salty; why then do you not give thanks"
  56,71,Do you not see the fire which you kindle
  56,72,"Is it you who made the tree thereof to grow, or are We the Grower"
  56,73,"We have made it a Reminder, and an article of use for the Muqwin"
  56,74,"Then glorify with praises the Name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  56,75,Fala! I swear by the Mawaqi` of the stars
  56,76,"And verily that is indeed a great oath, if you but know"
  56,77,That (this) is indeed an honorable recitation
  56,78,In a Book Maknun
  56,79,Which none touches but the pure ones
  56,80,A revelation from the Lord of all that exists
  56,81,Is it such a talk that you are Mudhinun
  56,82,And you make your provision your denial
  56,83,Then why do you not (intervene) when it reaches Al-Hulqum
  56,84,And you at the moment are looking
  56,85,"But We are nearer to him than you, but you see not"
  56,86,Then why do you not -- if you are not Madinin
  56,87,"Return the soul, if you are truthful"
  56,88,"Then, if he be of the Muqarrabin"
  56,89,"Then Rawh, Rayhan and a Garden of Delights"
  56,90,And if he be of those on the right
  56,91,Then Salam (peace) to you from those on the right
  56,92,"But if he be of the denying, the erring"
  56,93,Then for him is an entertainment with Hamim
  56,94,And entry in Hellfire
  56,95,"Verily, this! This is an absolute truth with certainty"
  56,96,"So, glorify with praises the Name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  57,1,"Whatever is in the heavens and the earth glorifies Allah -- and He is the Almighty, All-Wise"
  57,2,His is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. It is He Who gives life and causes death; and He is Able to do all things
  57,3,"He is Al-Awwal and Al-Akhir, Az-Zahir and Al-Batin. And He is the All-Knower of everything"
  57,4,"He it is Who created the heavens and the earth in six Days and then rose (Istawa) over the Throne. He knows what goes into the earth and what comes forth from it, and what descends from the heaven and what ascends thereto. And He is with you wheresoever you may be. And Allah is the All-Seer of what you do"
  57,5,His is the kingdom of the heavens and the earth. And to Allah return all the matters
  57,6,"He merges night into day, and merges day into night, and He has full knowledge of whatsoever is in the breasts"
  57,7,"Believe in Allah and His Messenger, and spend of that whereof He has made you trustees. And such of you as believe and spend, theirs will be a great reward"
  57,8,"And what is the matter with you that you believe not in Allah! While the Messenger invites you to believe in your Lord; and He has indeed taken your covenant, if you are real believers"
  57,9,"It is He Who sends down manifest Ayat to His servant that He may bring you out from darkness into light. And verily, Allah is to you full of kindness, Most Merciful"
  57,10,And what is the matter with you that you spend not in the cause of Allah And to Allah belongs the heritage of the heavens and the earth. Not equal among you are those who spent and fought before the conquering. Such are higher in degree than those who spent and fought afterwards. But to all Allah has promised the best. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do
  57,11,"Who is he that will lend Allah a handsome loan: then He will increase it manifold to his credit, and he will have a honorable reward"
  57,12,"On the Day you shall see the believing men and the believing women -- their light running forward before them and in their right hands. Glad tidings for you this Day! Gardens under which rivers flow (Paradise), to dwell therein forever! Truly, this is the great success"
  57,13,"On the Day when the hypocrites men and women will say to the believers: \"Wait for us! Let us get something from your light!\" It will be said: \"Go back to your rear! Then seek a light!\" So, a wall will be put up between them, with a gate therein. Inside it will be mercy, and outside it will be torment"
  57,14,"(The hypocrites) will call the believers: \"Were we not with you\" The believers will reply: \"Yes! But you led yourselves into temptations, you looked forward to our destruction; and you doubted, and you were deceived by false hopes, till the command of Allah came to pass. And the deceiver deceived you in regard to Allah"
  57,15,"So, this Day no ransom shall be taken from you, nor of those who disbelieved. Your abode is the Fire. That is your protector, and worst indeed is that destination"
  57,16,"Has not the time yet come for the believers that their hearts should be humble for the remembrance of Allah And that which has been revealed of the truth, lest they become as those who received the Scripture before, and the term was prolonged for them and so their hearts were hardened And many of them were rebellious"
  57,17,"Know that Allah gives life to the earth after its death! Indeed We have made clear the Ayat to you, if you but understand"
  57,18,"Verily, those who give Sadaqat, men and women, and lend Allah handsome loan, it shall be increased manifold (to their credit), and theirs shall be an honorable good reward"
  57,19,And those who believe in Allah and His Messengers. they are the Siddiqun (true believers) and the martyrs with their Lord. They shall have their reward and their light. But those who disbelieve and deny Our Ayat -- they shall be the dwellers of the blazing Fire
  57,20,"Know that the life of this world is only play and amusement, pomp and mutual boasting among you, and rivalry in respect of wealth and children. (It is) like a rain (Ghayth), thereof the growth is pleasing to the tiller; afterwards it dries up and you see it turning yellow; then it becomes straw. But in the Hereafter (there is) a severe torment, and (there is) forgiveness from Allah and (His) pleasure. And the life of this world is only a deceiving enjoyment"
  57,21,"Race with one another in hastening towards forgiveness from your Lord, and Paradise the width whereof is as the width of the heaven and the earth, prepared for those who believe in Allah and His Messengers. That is the grace of Allah which He bestows on whom He is pleased with. And Allah is the Owner of great bounty"
  57,22,"No calamity occurs in the earth nor in yourselves but it is inscribed in the Book of Decrees before We bring it into existence. Verily, that is easy for Allah"
  57,23,"In order that you may not grieve at the things over that you fail to get, nor rejoice over that which has been given to you. And Allah likes not prideful boasters"
  57,24,"Those who are misers and enjoin miserliness upon people. And whosoever turns away, then Allah is Rich, Worthy of all praise"
  57,25,"Indeed We have sent Our Messengers with clear proofs, and revealed with them the Scripture and the Mizan that mankind may keep up justice. And We brought forth iron wherein is mighty power, as well as many benefits for mankind, that Allah may test who it is that will help Him (His religion) and His Messengers in the unseen. Verily, Allah is Powerful, Almighty"
  57,26,"And indeed, We sent Nuh and Ibrahim, and placed in their offspring prophethood and Scripture. And among them there are some who are guided; but many of them are rebellious"
  57,27,"Then, We sent after them Our Messengers, and We sent `Isa the son of Maryam, and gave him the Injil. And We ordained in the hearts of those who followed him, compassion and mercy. But the monasticism which they invented for themselves, We did not prescribe for them, but (they sought it) only to please Allah therewith, but that they did not observe it with the right observance. So, We gave those among them who believed, their (due) reward; but many of them are rebellious"
  57,28,"O you who believe! Have Taqwa of Allah, and believe in His Messenger, He will give you a double portion of His mercy, and He will give you a light by which you shall walk (straight). And He will forgive you. And Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  57,29,"So that the People of the Scriptures may know that they have no power whatsoever over the grace of Allah, and that (His) grace is in His Hand to bestow it on whomsoever He wills. And Allah is the Owner of great bounty"
  58,1,"Indeed Allah has heard the statement of her that disputes with you concerning her husband, and complains to Allah. And Allah hears the argument between you both. Verily, Allah is All-Hearer, All-Seer"
  58,2,"Those among you who make their wives unlawful to them by Zihar they cannot be their mothers. None can be their mothers except those who gave them birth. And verily, they utter an ill word and a lie. And verily, Allah is Oft-Pardoning, Oft-Forgiving"
  58,3,"And those who make unlawful to them (their wives) by Zihar and wish to free themselves from what they uttered, (the penalty) in that case is the freeing of a slave before they touch each other. That is an admonition to you. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,4,"And he who finds not, must fast two successive months before they both touch each other. And he who is unable to do so, should feed sixty of the poor. That is in order that you may have perfect faith in Allah and His Messenger. These are the limits set by Allah. And for disbelievers, there is a painful torment"
  58,5,"Verily, those who oppose Allah and His Messenger will be disgraced as those before them were disgraced. And We have sent down clear Ayat. And for the disbelievers is a disgraceful torment"
  58,6,"On the Day when Allah will resurrect them all together and inform them of what they did. Allah has kept account of it, while they have forgotten it. And Allah is Witness over all things"
  58,7,"Have you not seen that Allah knows whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is on the earth There is no Najwa of three but He is their fourth nor of five but He is their sixth nor of less than that or more but He is with them wheresoever they may be. And afterwards on the Day of Resurrection He will inform them of what they did. Verily, Allah is the All-Knower of everything"
  58,8,"Have you not seen those who were forbidden to hold secret counsels, and afterwards returned to that which they had been forbidden, and conspired together for sin and wrongdoing and disobedience to the Messenger. And when they come to you, they greet you with a greeting wherewith Allah greets you not, and say within themselves: \"Why should Allah punish us not for what we say\" Hell will be sufficient for them; they will enter therein. And worst indeed is that destination"
  58,9,"O you who believe! When you hold secret counsel, do it not for sin and wrongdoing, and disobedience to the Messenger, but do it for Al-Birr and Taqwa; and have Taqwa of Allah unto Whom you shall be gathered"
  58,10,"Secret counsels are only from Shaytan, in order that he may cause grief to the believers. But he cannot harm them in the least, except as Allah permits. And in Allah let the believers put their trust"
  58,11,"O you who believe! When you are told to make room in the assemblies, make room. Allah will give you room. And when you are told to rise up, then rise up. Allah will exalt in degress those of you who believe, and those who have been granted knowledge. And Allah is Well-Acquainted with what you do"
  58,12,"O you who believe! When you (want to) consult the Messenger in private, spend something in charity before your private consultation. That will be better and purer for you. But if you find not (the means for it), then verily, Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  58,13,"Are you afraid of spending in charity before your private consultation (with him) If then you do it not, and Allah has forgiven you, then perform Salah and give Zakah and obey Allah and His Messenger. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  58,14,"Have you not seen those who take as friends a people upon whom is the wrath of Allah They are neither of you nor of them, and they swear to a lie while they know"
  58,15,Allah has prepared for them a severe torment. Evil indeed is that which they used to do
  58,16,"They have made their oaths a screen. Thus they hinder (others) from the path of Allah, so they shall have a humiliating torment"
  58,17,Their children and their wealth will avail them nothing against Allah. They will be the dwellers of the Fire to dwell therein forever
  58,18,"On the Day when Allah will resurrect them all together; then they will swear to Him as they swear to you. And they think that they have something. Verily, they are liars"
  58,19,"The Shaytan has overpowered them. So he has made them forget the remembrance of Allah. They are the party of Shaytan. Verily, it is the party of Shaytan that will be the losers"
  58,20,"Those who oppose Allah and His Messenger, they will be among those most humiliated"
  58,21,"Allah has decreed: \"Verily, I and My Messengers shall be the victorious.\" Verily, Allah is All-Powerful, Almighty"
  58,22,"You will not find any people who believe in Allah and the Last Day, making friendship with those who oppose Allah and His Messenger, even though they were their fathers or their sons or their brothers or their kindred. For such He has written faith in their hearts, and strengthened them with Ruh from Himself. And He will admit them to Gardens under which rivers flow, to dwell therein (forever). Allah is well pleased with them, and they are well pleased with Him. They are the party of Allah. Verily, the party of Allah will be the successful"
  59,1,"Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is on the earth glorifies Allah. And He is the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  59,2,"He it is Who drove out the disbelievers among the People of the Scripture from their homes at the first gathering. You did not think that they would get out. And they thought that their fortresses would defend them from Allah! But Allah reached them from a place whereof they expected it not, and He cast terror into their hearts so that they demolished their own dwellings with their own hands and the hands of the believers. Then take admonition, O you with eyes"
  59,3,"And had it not been that Allah had decreed exile for them, He would certainly have punished them in this world; and in the Hereafter theirs shall be the torment of the Fire"
  59,4,"That is because they opposed Allah and His Messenger. And whosoever opposes Allah, then verily, Allah is Severe in punishment"
  59,5,"What you cut down of the Linah, or you left them standing on their stems, it was by leave of Allah, and in order that He might disgrace the rebellious"
  59,6,And what Allah gave as booty (Fai') to His Messenger from them -- for this you made no expedition with either cavalry or camelry. But Allah gives power to His Messengers over whomsoever He wills. And Allah is Able to do all things
  59,7,"What Allah gave as booty (Fai') to His Messenger from the people of the townships -- it is for Allah, His Messenger, the kindred, the orphans, the poor, and the wayfarer, in order that it may not become a fortune used by the rich among you. And whatsoever the Messenger gives you, take it; and whatsoever he forbids you, abstain (from it). And have Taqwa of Allah, verily, Allah is Severe in punishment"
  59,8,"(And there is also a share in this booty) for the poor emigrants, who were expelled from their homes and their property, seeking bounties from Allah and (His) good pleasure, and helping Allah and His Messenger. Such are indeed the truthful"
  59,9,"And (it is also for) those who, before them, had homes and had adopted the faith, love those who emigrate to them, and have no jealousy in their breasts for that which they have been given, and give them preference over themselves even though they were in need of that. And whosoever is saved from his own greed, such are they who will be the successful"
  59,10,"And those who came after them say: \"Our Lord! Forgive us and our brethren who have preceded us in faith, and put not in our hearts any hatred against those who have believed. Our Lord! You are indeed full of kindness, Most Merciful"
  59,11,"Have you not observed the hypocrites who say to their disbelieving brethren among the People of the Scripture, \"If you are expelled, we indeed will go out with you, and we shall never obey anyone against you; and if you are attacked, we shall indeed help you.\" But Allah is Witness that they verily are liars"
  59,12,"Surely, if they (the Jews) are expelled, never will they (hypocrites) go out with them; and if they are attacked, they will never help them. And (even) if they do help them, they (hypocrites) will turn their backs, and they will not be victorious"
  59,13,"Verily, you are more fearful in their breasts than Allah. That is because they are a people who comprehend not"
  59,14,"They fight not against you even together, except in fortified townships, or from behind walls. Their enmity among themselves is very great. You would think they were united, but their hearts are divided. That is because they are a people who understand not"
  59,15,"They are like their immediate predecessors; they tasted the evil result of their conduct, and for them a painful torment"
  59,16,"Like Shaytan, when he says to man: \"Disbelieve.\" But when he disbelieves, Shaytan says: \"I am free of you, I fear Allah, the Lord of all that exists"
  59,17,"So, the end of both will be that they will be in the Fire, abiding therein. Such is the recompense of the wrongdoers"
  59,18,"O you who believe! Have Taqwa of Allah and let every person look to what he has sent forth for tomorrow, and fear Allah. Verily, Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  59,19,"And be not like those who forgot Allah, and He caused them to forget themselves. Those are the rebellious"
  59,20,Not equal are the dwellers of the Fire and the dwellers of the Paradise. It is the dwellers of Paradise that will be successful
  59,21,"Had We sent down this Qur'an on a mountain, you would surely have seen it humbling itself and rent asunder by the fear of Allah. Such are the parables which We put forward to mankind that they may reflect"
  59,22,"He is Allah, beside Whom La ilaha illa Huwa, the All-Knower of the unseen and the seen. He is the Most Gracious, the Most Merciful"
  59,23,"He is Allah, beside Whom La ilaha illa Huwa, Al-Malik, Al-Quddus, As-Salam, Al-Mu`min, Al-Muhaymin, Al-`Aziz, Al-Jabbar, Al-Mutakabbir. Glory be to Allah! Above all that they associate as partners with Him"
  59,24,"He is Allah, Al-Khaliq, Al-Bari, Al-Musawwir. To Him belong the Best Names. All that is in the heavens and the earth glorify Him. And He is the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  60,1,"O you who believe! Take not My enemies and your enemies as protecting friends, showing affection towards them, while they have disbelieved in what has come to you of the truth, and have driven out the Messenger and yourselves because you believe in Allah, your Lord! If you have come forth to strive in My cause and to seek My good pleasure. You show friendship to them in secret, while I am All-Aware of what you conceal and what you reveal. And whosoever of you (Muslims) does that, then indeed he has gone (far) astray from the straight path"
  60,2,"Should they gain the upper hand over you, they would behave to you as enemies, and stretch forth their hands and their tongues against you with evil, and they desire that you should disbelieve"
  60,3,Neither your relatives nor your children will benefit you on the Day of Resurrection. He will judge between you. And Allah is the All-Seer of what you do
  60,4,"Indeed there has been an excellent example for you in Ibrahim and those with him, when they said to their people: \"Verily, we are free from you and whatever you worship besides Allah, we have rejected you, and there has started between us and you, hostility and hatred forever until you believe in Allah alone,\" -- except the saying of Ibrahim to his father: \"Verily, I will ask forgiveness for you, but I have no power to do anything for you before Allah.\" \"Our Lord! In You we put our trust, and to You we turn in repentance, and to You is the final Return"
  60,5,"Our Lord! Make us not a trial for the disbelievers, and forgive us, Our Lord! Verily, You, only You, are the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  60,6,"Certainly, there has been in them an excellent example for you to follow - for those who look forward to (the meeting with) Allah and the Last Day. And whosoever turns away, then verily, Allah is Al-Ghani, Al-Hamid"
  60,7,"Perhaps Allah will make friendship between you and those whom you hold as enemies. And Allah has power (over all things), and Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  60,8,"Allah does not forbid you to deal justly and kindly with those who fought not against you on account of religion nor drove you out of your homes. Verily, Allah loves those who deal with equity"
  60,9,"It is only as regards those who fought against you on account of religion, and have driven you out of your homes, and helped to drive you out, that Allah forbids you to befriend them. And whosoever will befriend them, then such are the wrongdoers"
  60,10,"O you who believe! When believing women come to you as emigrants, examine them; Allah knows best as to their faith, then if you ascertain that they are true believers, send them not back to the disbelievers. They are not lawful for the disbelievers nor are the disbelievers lawful for them. But give them (disbelievers) that which they have spent (on their dowery). And there will be no sin on you to marry them if you have paid their due to them. Likewise do not keep the disbelieving women, and ask for that which you have spent (on their dowery) and let them (the disbelievers) ask for that which they have spent. That is the judgement of Allah, He judges between you. And Allah is All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  60,11,"And if any of your wives have gone from you to the disbelievers then you succeed over them (gain victory); then pay those whose wives have gone, the equivalent of what they had spent. And have Taqwa of Allah, the One in Whom you are believers"
  60,12,"O Prophet! When the believing women come to you pledging to you that they will not associate anything with Allah, and that they will not steal, and that they will not commit Zina, and that they will not kill their children, and that they will not utter slander, fabricating from between their hands and their feet, and that they will not disobey you in Ma`ruf (good), Allah said to the faithful believers"
  60,13,"O you who believe! Take not as friends the people who incurred the wrath of Allah. Surely, they have despaired of the Hereafter, just as the disbelievers have despaired of those (buried) in graves"
  61,1,"Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is on the earth glorifies Allah. And He is the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  61,2,O you who believe! Why do you say that which you do not do
  61,3,Most hateful it is with Allah that you say that which you do not do
  61,4,"Verily, Allah loves those who fight in His cause in rows as if they were a solid structure"
  61,5,"And when Musa said to his people: \"O my people! Why do you annoy me while you know certainly that I am the Messenger of Allah to you So, when they turned away (from the path of Allah), Allah turned their hearts away (from the right path). And Allah guides not the people who are rebellious"
  61,6,"And (remember) when `Isa, son of Maryam, said: \"O Children of Israel! I am the Messenger of Allah unto you, confirming the Tawrah [which came] before me, and giving glad tidings of a Messenger to come after me, whose name shall be Ahmad. \"But when he came to them with clear proofs, they said: \"This is plain magic"
  61,7,"And who does more wrong than the one who invents a lie against Allah, while he is being invited to Islam And Allah guides not the people who are wrongdoers"
  61,8,They intend to put out the Light of Allah with their mouths. But Allah will bring His Light to perfection even though the disbelievers hate (it)
  61,9,He it is Who has sent His Messenger with guidance and the religion of truth to make it victorious over all religions even though idolators hate (it)
  61,10,O you who believe! Shall I guide you to a trade that will save you from a painful torment
  61,11,"That you believe in Allah and His Messenger, and that you strive hard and fight in the cause of Allah with your wealth and your lives, that will be better for you, if you but know"
  61,12,"(If you do so) He will forgive you your sins, and admit you into Gardens under which rivers flow, and pleasant dwellings in `Adn (Eternal) Paradise; that is indeed the great success"
  61,13,"And also (He will give you) another (blessing) which you love, help from Allah and a near victory. And give glad tidings to the believers"
  61,14,"O you who believe! Be you helpers (in the cause) of Allah as said `Isa, son of Maryam, to the Hawariyyin (the disciples): \"Who are my helpers (in the cause) of Allah\" The Hawariyyun said: \"We are Allah's helpers\" (i.e., we will strive in His cause!). Then a group of the Children of Israel believed and a group disbelieved. So, We gave power to those who believed against their enemies, and they became the victorious (uppermost)"
  62,1,"Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is on the earth glorifies Allah -- the King, the Holy, the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  62,2,"He it is Who sent among the unlettered ones a Messenger from among themselves, reciting to them His Ayat, purifying them, and teaching them the Book and the Hikmah. And verily, they had been before in manifest error"
  62,3,"And others among them who have not yet joined them. And He is the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  62,4,"That is the grace of Allah, which He bestows on whom He wills. And Allah is the Owner of mighty grace"
  62,5,"The likeness of those who were entrusted with the Tawrah, but did not carry it, is as the likeness of a donkey which carries huge burdens of books. How bad is the example of people who deny the Ayat of Allah. And Allah does not guide the people who are wrongdoers"
  62,6,"Say: \"O you Jews! If you pretend that you are friends of Allah, to the exclusion of (all) other people, then long for death if you are truthful"
  62,7,"But they will never long for it, because of what their hands have sent before them! And Allah knows well the wrongdoers"
  62,8,"Say: \"Verily, the death from which you flee, will surely meet you, then you will be sent back to the Knower of the unseen and the seen, and He will inform you about what you used to do"
  62,9,"O you who believe! When the call is proclaimed for the Salah on Al-Jumu`ah (Friday), then hasten (Fas`aw) to the remembrance of Allah and leave off business. That is better for you if you did but know"
  62,10,"Then when the Salah is complete, you may disperse through the land, and seek the bounty of Allah, and remember Allah much, that you may be successful"
  62,11,"And when they see some merchandise or some amusement, they disperse headlong to it, and leave you standing. Say: \"That which Allah has is better than any amusement or merchandise! And Allah is the best of providers"
  63,1,"When the hypocrites come to you, they say: \"We bear witness that you are indeed the Messenger of Allah.\" Allah knows that you are indeed His Messenger, and Allah bears witness that the hypocrites are liars indeed"
  63,2,"They have made their oaths a screen. Thus they hinder (others) from the path of Allah. Verily, evil is what they used to do"
  63,3,"That is because they believed, and then disbelieved; therefore their hearts are sealed, so they understand not"
  63,4,"And when you look at them, their bodies please you; and when they speak, you listen to their words. They are as blocks of wood propped up. They think that every cry is against them. They are the enemies, so beware of them. May Allah curse them! How are they denying the right path"
  63,5,"And when it is said to them: \"Come, so that the Messenger of Allah may ask forgiveness from Allah for you,\" they twist their heads, and you would see them turning away their faces in pride"
  63,6,"It is equal to them whether you ask forgiveness or ask not forgiveness for them, Allah will never forgive them. Verily, Allah guides not the people who are the rebellious"
  63,7,"They are the ones who say: \"Spend not on those who are with Allah's Messenger, until they desert him.\" And to Allah belong the treasures of the heavens and the earth, but the hypocrites comprehend not"
  63,8,"They say: \"If we return to Al-Madinah, indeed the more honorable will expel therefrom the weaker.\" But Al-`Izzah belongs to Allah, and to His Messenger, and to the believers, but the hypocrites know not"
  63,9,"O you who believe! Let not your properties or your children divert you from the remembrance of Allah. And whosoever does that, then they are the losers"
  63,10,"And spend of that with which We have provided you before death comes to one of you, and he says: \"My Lord! If only You would give me respite for a little while, then I should give Sadaqah from my wealth, and be among the righteous"
  63,11,And Allah grants respite to none when his appointed time comes. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do
  64,1,"Whatsoever is in the heavens and whatsoever is on the earth glorifies Allah. His is the dominion, and to Him belongs the praise, and He is Able to do all things"
  64,2,"He it is Who created you, then some of you are disbelievers and some of you are believers. And Allah is All-Seer of what you do"
  64,3,"He has created the heavens and the earth with truth, and He shaped you and made good your shapes. And to Him is the return"
  64,4,"He knows what is in the heavens and on earth, and He knows what you conceal and what you reveal. And Allah is the All-Knower of what is in the breasts"
  64,5,"Has not the news reached you of those who disbelieved aforetime And so they tasted the evil result of their disbelief, and theirs will be a painful torment"
  64,6,"That was because there came to them their Messengers with Bayyinat, but they said: \"Shall mere men guide us\" So they disbelieved and turned away. But Allah was not in need. And Allah is not in need, Worthy of all praise"
  64,7,"The disbelievers pretend that they will never be resurrected. Say: \"Yes! By my Lord, you will certainly be resurrected, then you will be informed of what you did; and that is easy for Allah"
  64,8,"Therefore, believe in Allah and His Messenger and in the Light which We have sent down. And Allah is All-Aware of what you do"
  64,9,"The Day when He will gather you on the Day of Gathering, that will be the Day of At-Taghabun. And whosoever believes in Allah and performs righteous deeds, He will expiate from him his sins, and will admit him to Gardens beneath which rivers flow, to dwell therein forever; that will be the great success"
  64,10,"But those who disbelieved and denied Our Ayat, they will be the dwellers of the Fire, to dwell therein forever. And worst indeed is that destination"
  64,11,"No calamity occurs, but by the permission of Allah, and whosoever believes in Allah, He guides his heart. And Allah is the All-Knower of everything"
  64,12,"Obey Allah, and obey the Messenger; but if you turn away, then the duty of Our Messenger is only to convey clearly"
  64,13,Allah! La ilaha illa Huwa. And in Allah therefore let the believers put their trust
  64,14,"O you who believe! Verily, among your wives and your children there are enemies for you; therefore beware of them! But if you pardon (them) and overlook, and forgive, then verily, Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  64,15,"Your wealth and your children are only a Fitnah, whereas Allah! With Him is a great reward"
  64,16,"So have Taqwa of Allah as much as you can; listen and obey, and spend in charity; that is better for yourselves. And whosoever is saved from his own greed, then they are the successful ones"
  64,17,"If you lend to Allah a handsome loan, He will double it for you, and will forgive you. And Allah is Shakur, Halim"
  64,18,"All-Knower of the unseen and seen, the Almighty, the All-Wise"
  65,1,"O Prophet! When you divorce women, divorce them at their `Iddah and count their `Iddah. And have Taqwa of Allah, your Lord. And turn them not out of their homes nor shall they leave, except in case they are guilty of Fahishah Mubayyinah. And those are the set limits of Allah. And whosoever transgresses the set limits of Allah, then indeed he has wronged himself. You know not, it may be that Allah will afterward bring some new thing to pass"
  65,2,"Then when they are about to attain their term appointed, either take them back in a good manner or part with them in a good manner. And take as witness two just persons from among you. And establish the testimony for Allah. That will be an admonition given to him who believes in Allah and the Last Day. And whosoever has Taqwa of Allah, He will make a way for him to get out"
  65,3,"And He will provide him from where he never could imagine. And whosoever puts his trust in Allah, then He will suffice him. Verily, Allah will accomplish his purpose. Indeed Allah has set a measure for all things"
  65,4,"Those in menopause among your women, for them the `Iddah, if you have doubt, is three months; and for those who have no courses. And for those who are pregnant, their `Iddah is until they lay down their burden; and whosoever has Taqwa of Allah, He will make his matter easy for him"
  65,5,"That is the command of Allah, which He has sent down to you; and whosoever has Taqwa of Allah, He will expiate from him his sins, and will increase his reward"
  65,6,"Lodge them where you dwell, according to what you have, and do not harm them so as to suppress them. And if they are pregnant, then spend on them till they lay down their burden. Then if they suckle the children for you, give them their due payment, and let each of you deal with each other in a mannerly way. But if you make difficulties for one another, then some other woman may suckle for him"
  65,7,"Let the rich man spend according to his means; and the man whose resources are restricted, let him spend according to what Allah has given him. Allah puts no burden on any person beyond what He has given him. Allah will grant after hardship, ease"
  65,8,"And many a town revolted against the command of its Lord and His Messengers; and We called it to a severe account, and We shall punish it with a horrible torment"
  65,9,"So it tasted the evil result of its affair, and the consequence of its affair was loss"
  65,10,"Allah has prepared for them a severe torment. So have Taqwa of Allah, O men of understanding, those who believe! Allah has indeed sent down to you a Reminder"
  65,11,"A Messenger, who recites to you the Ayat of Allah containing clear explanations, that He may take out those who believe and do righteous good deeds, from the darkness to the light. And whosoever believes in Allah and performs righteous deeds, He will admit him into Gardens under which rivers flow, to dwell therein forever. Allah has indeed granted for him an excellent provision"
  65,12,"It is Allah Who has created seven heavens and of the earth the like thereof. His command descends between them, that you may know that Allah has power over all things, and that Allah surrounds all things with (His) knowledge"
  66,1,"O Prophet! Why do you forbid that which Allah has allowed to you, seeking to please your wives And Allah is Oft-Forgiving, Most Merciful"
  66,2,"Allah has already ordained for you (O men) the absolution from your oaths. And Allah is your Protector and He is the All-Knower, the All-Wise"
  66,3,"And (remember) when the Prophet disclosed a matter in confidence to one of his wives, then she told it. And Allah made it known to him; he informed part thereof and left a part. Then when he told her thereof, she said: \"Who told you this\" He said: \"The All-Knower, the All-Aware has told me"
  66,4,"If you two turn in repentance to Allah, your hearts are indeed so inclined; but if you help one another against him, then verily, Allah is his Protector, and Jibril, and the righteous among the believers; and after that the angels are his helpers"
  66,5,"Maybe his Lord, if he divorces you, will give him instead of you, wives better than you - submitting, believers, obedient, turning to Allah in repentance, worshipping Allah sincerely, Sa'ihat, previously married, and virgins"
  66,6,"O you who believe! Protect yourselves and your families against a Fire (Hell) whose fuel is men and stones, over which are (appointed) angels stern (and) severe, who disobey not the commands they receive from Allah, but do that which they are commanded"
  66,7,(It will be said in the Hereafter) O you who disbelieve! Make no excuses this Day! You are being requited only for what you used to do
  66,8,"O you who believe! Turn to Allah with sincere repentance! It may be that your Lord will expiate from you your sins, and admit you into Gardens under which rivers flow -- the Day that Allah will not disgrace the Prophet and those who believe with him. Their light will run forward before them and in their right hands. They will say: \"Our Lord! Keep perfect our light for us and grant us forgiveness. Verily, You are Able to do all things"
  66,9,"O Prophet! Strive hard against the disbelievers and the hypocrites, and be severe against them; their abode will be Hell, and worst indeed is that destination"
  66,10,"Allah sets forth an example for those who disbelieve: the wife of Nuh and the wife of Lut. They were under two of our righteous servants, but they both betrayed them. So, they availed them not against Allah and it was said: \"Enter the Fire along with those who enter"
  66,11,"And Allah has set forth an example for those who believe: the wife of Fir`awn, when she said: \"My Lord! Build for me a home with You in Paradise, and save me from Fir`awn and his work, and save me from the people who are wrongdoers"
  66,12,"And Maryam, the daughter of `Imran who guarded her chastity (private part). And We breathed into it through Our Ruh, and she testified to the truth of her Lords Kalimat, and His Kutub, and she was of the Qanitin"
  67,1,Blessed be He in Whose Hand is the dominion; and He is Able to do all things
  67,2,"Who has created death and life that He may test you which of you is best in deed. And He is the Almighty, the Oft-Forgiving"
  67,3,Who has created the seven heavens one above the other; you can see no fault in the creation of the Most Gracious. Then look again. Can you see any rifts
  67,4,"Then look again and yet again, your sight will return to you Khasi', and worn out"
  67,5,"And indeed We have adorned the nearest heaven with lamps, and We have made such lamps (as) missiles to drive away the Shayatin, and have prepared for them the torment of the blazing Fire"
  67,6,"And for those who disbelieve in their Lord is the torment of Hell, and worst indeed is that destination"
  67,7,"When they are cast therein, they will hear its Shahiq while it is simmering"
  67,8,"It almost bursts up with fury. Every time a group is cast therein, its keepers will ask: \"Did no warner come to you"
  67,9,"They will say: \"Yes, indeed a warner did come to us, but we rejected him and said: `Allah never sent down anything; you are only in great error"
  67,10,"And they will say: \"Had we but listened or used our intelligence, we would not have been among the dwellers of the blazing Fire"
  67,11,"Then they will confess their sin. So, away with the dwellers of the blazing Fire"
  67,12,"Verily, those who fear their Lord unseen, theirs will be forgiveness and a great reward"
  67,13,"And whether you keep your talk secret or disclose it, verily, He is the All-Knower of what is in the breasts"
  67,14,"Should not He Who has created know And He is the Most Kind and Courteous, All-Aware"
  67,15,He it is Who has made the earth subservient to you; so walk in the paths thereof and eat of His provision. And to Him will be the resurrection
  67,16,"Do you feel secure that He, Who is over the heaven, will not cause the earth to sink with you, and then it should quake"
  67,17,"Or do you feel secure that He, Who is over the heaven, will not send against you a Hasib Then you shall know how has been My warning"
  67,18,"And indeed those before them rejected, then how terrible was My reproach"
  67,19,"Do they not see the birds above them, spreading out their wings and folding them in None upholds them except the Most Gracious. Verily, He is the All-Seer of everything"
  67,20,Who is it besides the Most Gracious that can be an army to you to help you The disbelievers are in nothing but delusion
  67,21,"Who is it that can provide for you if He should withhold His provision Nay, but they continue to be in pride, and flee"
  67,22,"Is he who walks prone on his face, more rightly guided, or he who walks upright on a straight path"
  67,23,"Say: \"It is He Who has created you, and endowed you with hearing and seeing, and hearts. Little thanks you give"
  67,24,"Say: \"It is He Who has created you on the earth, and to Him shall you be gathered"
  67,25,"They say: \"When will this promise come to pass, if you are telling the truth"
  67,26,"Say: \"The knowledge is with Allah only, and I am only a plain warner"
  67,27,"But when they will see it approaching, the faces of those who disbelieve will be sad and grievous, and it will be said: \"This is what you were calling for"
  67,28,"Say: \"Tell me! If Allah destroys me, and those with me, or He bestows His mercy on us - who can save the disbelievers from a painful torment"
  67,29,"Say: \"He is the Most Gracious, in Him we believe, and upon Him we rely. So, you will come to know who it is that is in manifest error"
  67,30,"Say: \"Tell me! If (all) your water were to sink away, who then can supply you with flowing water"
  68,1,Nun. By the pen and by what they Yastur
  68,2,"You, by the grace of your Lord, are not insane"
  68,3,"And verily, for you will be reward that is not Mamnun"
  68,4,"And verily, you are on an exalted character"
  68,5,"You will see, and they will see"
  68,6,Which of you is afflicted with madness
  68,7,"Verily, your Lord is the best Knower of him who has gone astray from His path, and He is the best Knower of those who are guided"
  68,8,"So, do not obey the deniers"
  68,9,"They wish that you should compromise with them, so they (too) would compromise with you"
  68,10,And do not obey every Hallaf Mahin
  68,11,"A Hammaz, going about with Namim"
  68,12,"Hinderer of the good, transgressor, sinful"
  68,13,"Utul, and moreover Zanim"
  68,14,(He was so) because he had wealth and children
  68,15,"When Our Ayat are recited to him, he says: \"Tales of the men of old"
  68,16,We shall brand him on the snout (nose)
  68,17,"Verily, We have tried them as We tried the People of the Garden, when they swore to pluck the fruits in the morning"
  68,18,"Without saying: \"If Allah wills"
  68,19,Then there passed over it a Ta'if from your Lord while they were asleep
  68,20,"So by the morning, it became like As-Sarim"
  68,21,Then they called out (one to another as soon) as the morning broke
  68,22,"Saying: \"Go to your tilth in the morning, if you would pluck (the fruits)"
  68,23,"So they departed, and they were whispering"
  68,24,No poor person shall enter upon you into it today
  68,25,And they went in the morning with Hard Qadirin
  68,26,"But when they saw it, they said: \"Verily, we have gone astray"
  68,27,Nay! Indeed we are deprived
  68,28,"The Awsat among them said; \"Did I not tell you, `Why do you not Tusabbihun"
  68,29,"They said: \"Glory to Our Lord! Verily, we have been wrongdoers"
  68,30,"Then they turned one against another, blaming"
  68,31,"They said: \"Woe to us! Verily, we were Taghin"
  68,32,"We hope that our Lord will give us in exchange better than it. Truly, we hope in our Lord"
  68,33,"Such is the punishment, but truly, the punishment of the Hereafter is greater if they but knew"
  68,34,"Verily, for those who have Taqwa are Gardens of Delight with their Lord"
  68,35,Shall We then treat the Muslims like the criminals
  68,36,What is the matter with you How judge you
  68,37,Or have you a Book wherein you learn
  68,38,That you shall therein have all that you choose
  68,39,"Or have you oaths from Us, lasting until the Day of Judgement, that yours will be what you judge"
  68,40,"Ask them, which of them will stand as surety for that"
  68,41,"Or have they \"partners\" Then let them bring their \"partners\" if they are truthful"
  68,42,"The Day when the Shin shall be laid bare and they shall be called to prostrate themselves, but they shall not be able to do so"
  68,43,"Their eyes will be cast down and ignominy will cover them; they used to be called to prostrate themselves, while they were"
  68,44,Then leave Me alone with whoever denies this narration. We shall punish them gradually from directions they perceive not
  68,45,"And I will grant them a respite. Verily, My plan is strong"
  68,46,"Or is it that you ask them a wage, so that they are heavily burdened with debt"
  68,47,"Or that the Unseen is in their hands, so that they can write it down"
  68,48,"So, wait with patience for the decision of your Lord, and be not like the Companion of the Fish when he cried out (to Us) while he was Makzum"
  68,49,"Had not a grace from his Lord reached him, he would indeed have been (left in the stomach of the fish, but We forgave him), so he was cast off on the naked shore, while he was to be blamed"
  68,50,Then his Lord chose him and made him of the righteous
  68,51,"And verily, those who disbelieve would almost make you slip with their eyes (through hatred) when they hear the Reminder (the Qur'an), and they say: \"Verily, he is a madman"
  68,52,But it is nothing else than a Reminder to all the creatures (`Alamin)
  69,1,Al-Haqqah
  69,2,What is Al-Haqqah
  69,3,And what will make you know what Al-Haqqah is
  69,4,Thamud and `Ad denied the Qari`ah
  69,5,"As for Thamud, they were destroyed by the Taghiyah"
  69,6,"And as for `Ad, they were destroyed by a wind, Sarsar `Atiyah"
  69,7,"Which Allah imposed on them for seven nights and eight days Husum, so that you could see men lying toppled, as if they were trunks of date palms, Khawiyah"
  69,8,Do you see any remnants of them
  69,9,"And Fir`awn, and those before him, and the cities overthrown committed Al-Khati'ah"
  69,10,"And they disobeyed their Lord's Messenger, so He seized them with a punishment that was Rabiyah"
  69,11,"Verily, when the water rose beyond its limits, We carried you in the ship"
  69,12,That We might make it an admonition for you and that it might be retained by the retaining ears
  69,13,Then when the Trumpet will be blown with one blowing
  69,14,"And the earth and the mountains shall be removed from their places, and crushed with a single crushing"
  69,15,Then on that Day shall the Event occur
  69,16,"And the heaven will be rent asunder, for that Day it will be frail and torn up"
  69,17,"And the angels will be on its sides, and eight angels will, that Day, bear the Throne of your Lord above them"
  69,18,"That Day shall you be brought to Judgement, not a secret of you will be hidden"
  69,19,"Then as for him who will be given his Record in his right hand will say: \"Here! read my Record"
  69,20,"Surely, I did believe that I shall meet my account"
  69,21,"So, he shall be in a life, well-pleasing"
  69,22,In a lofty Paradise
  69,23,The fruits in bunches whereof will be low and near at hand
  69,24,Eat and drink at ease for that which you have sent on before you in days past
  69,25,"But as for him who will be given his Record in his left hand, will say: \"I wish that I had not been given my Record"
  69,26,And that I had never known how my account is
  69,27,Would that it had been my end
  69,28,My wealth has not availed me
  69,29,My power has gone from me
  69,30,"(It will be said): \"Seize him and fetter him"
  69,31,Then throw him in the blazing Fire
  69,32,Then fasten him on a chain whereof the length is seventy cubits
  69,33,"Verily, he used not to believe in Allah, the Most Great"
  69,34,And urged not the feeding of the poor
  69,35,"So, no friend has he here this Day"
  69,36,Nor any food except filth from Ghislin
  69,37,None will eat it except the Khati'un
  69,38,"So, I swear by whatsoever you see"
  69,39,And by whatsoever you see not
  69,40,That this is verily the word of an honored Messenger
  69,41,"It is not the word of a poet, little is that you believe"
  69,42,"Nor is it the word of a soothsayer, little is that you remember"
  69,43,This is the revelation sent down from the Lord of all that exists
  69,44,And if he had forged a false saying concerning Us
  69,45,We surely would have seized him by his right hand
  69,46,And then We certainly would have cut off Al-Watin from him
  69,47,And none of you could have prevented it from him
  69,48,"And verily, this is a Reminder for those who have Taqwa"
  69,49,"And verily, We know that there are some among you that deny"
  69,50,And indeed it will be an anguish for the disbelievers
  69,51,"And verily, it (this Qur'an) is an absolute truth with certainty"
  69,52,"So, glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most Great"
  70,1,A questioner asked concerning a torment about to befall
  70,2,"Upon the disbelievers, which none can avert"
  70,3,"From Allah, the Lord of the ways of ascent"
  70,4,The angels and the Ruh ascend to Him in a Day the measure whereof is fifty thousand years
  70,5,"So be patient, with a good patience"
  70,6,"Verily, they see it (the torment) afar off"
  70,7,But We see it near
  70,8,The Day that the sky will be like the Al-Muhl
  70,9,And the mountains will be like `Ihn
  70,10,And no friend will ask a friend
  70,11,"Though they shall be made to see one another, the criminal would desire to ransom himself from the punishment of that Day by his children"
  70,12,And his wife and his brother
  70,13,And his Fasilah who sheltered him
  70,14,"And all that are in the earth, so that it might save him"
  70,15,"By no means! Verily, it will be the fire of Hell"
  70,16,Nazza`ah the Shawa
  70,17,Calling (all) such as turn their backs and turn away their faces
  70,18,And collect (wealth) and hide it (from spending it in the cause of Allah)
  70,19,"Verily, man was created very impatient"
  70,20,Apprehensive when evil touches him
  70,21,And suppressive when good touches him
  70,22,Except those who are devoted to Salah
  70,23,Those who with their Salah are Da'imun
  70,24,And those in whose wealth there is a recognized right
  70,25,"For the one who asks, and for the deprived"
  70,26,And those who believe in the Day of Recompense
  70,27,And those who fear the torment of their Lord
  70,28,"Verily, the torment of their Lord is that before which none can feel secure"
  70,29,And those who guard their private part (chastity)
  70,30,Except from their wives or their right hand possessions -- for (then) they are not blameworthy
  70,31,"But whosoever seeks beyond that, then it is those who are trespassers"
  70,32,And those who keep their trusts and covenants
  70,33,And those who stand firm in their testimonies
  70,34,"And those who are with their Salah, Yuhafizun"
  70,35,"Such shall dwell in the Gardens, honored"
  70,36,"So, what is the matter with those disbelievers, before you Muhti`in"
  70,37,"On the right and on the left, `Izin"
  70,38,Does every man of them hope to enter the Paradise of Delight
  70,39,"But no! Verily, We have created them out of that which they know"
  70,40,But no! I swear by the Lord of the easts and the wests that surely We are Able
  70,41,To replace them by (others) better than them; and We are not to be outrun
  70,42,"So, leave them to plunge in vain talk and play about, until they meet their Day which they are promised"
  70,43,The Day when they will come out of the graves quickly as racing to a Nusub
  70,44,"With their eyes lowered in fear and humility, ignominy covering them (all over)! That is the Day which they were promised"
  71,1,"Verily, We sent Nuh to his people (saying): \"Warn your people before there comes to them a painful torment"
  71,2,"He said: \"O my people! Verily, I am a plain warner to you"
  71,3,"That you should worship Allah, and have Taqwa of Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"He will forgive you of your sins and respite you to an appointed term. Verily, the term of Allah when it comes, cannot be delayed, if you but know"
  71,5,"He said: O my Lord! Verily, I have called to my people night and day"
  71,6,But all my calling added nothing but to (their) flight
  71,7,"And verily, every time I called unto them that You might forgive them, they thrust their fingers into their ears, covered themselves up with their garments, and persisted, and magnified themselves in pride"
  71,8,"Then verily, I called to them openly (aloud)"
  71,9,"Then verily, I proclaimed to them in public, and I have appealed to them in private"
  71,10,"I said (to them): Ask forgiveness from your Lord, verily, He is Oft-Forgiving"
  71,11,He will send rain to you Midrar
  71,12,"And give you increase in wealth and children, and bestow on you gardens and bestow on you rivers"
  71,13,"What is the matter with you, that you do not hope for any Waqar from Allah"
  71,14,While He has created you (in) Atwar (stages)
  71,15,See you not how Allah has created the seven heavens in tiers
  71,16,"And has made the moon a light therein, and made the sun a lamp"
  71,17,And Allah has brought you forth from the (dust of) earth
  71,18,"Afterwards He will return you into it (the earth), and bring you forth"
  71,19,And Allah has made for you the earth a wide expanse
  71,20,That you may go about therein in broad roads
  71,21,"Nuh said: \"My Lord! They have disobeyed me, and followed one whose wealth and children give him no increase but loss"
  71,22,And they have plotted a mighty plot
  71,23,"And they have said: `You shall not leave your gods, nor shall you leave Wadd, nor Suwa`, nor Yaghuth, and Ya`uq and Nasr"
  71,24,"And indeed they have led many astray. And (O Allah): `Grant no increase to the wrongdoers save error"
  71,25,"Because of their sins they were drowned, then were made to enter the Fire. And they found none to help them instead of Allah"
  71,26,"And Nuh said: \"My Lord! Leave not one of the disbelievers on the earth Dayyar"
  71,27,"If You leave them, they will mislead Your servants, and they will beget none but wicked disbelievers"
  71,28,"(My Lord! Forgive me, and my parents, and him who enters my home as a believer, and all the believing men and women. And to the wrongdoers grant You no increase but destruction!\") Allah says"
  72,1,"Say: \"It has been revealed to me that a group of Jinn listened. They said: `Verily, we have heard a wonderful Recitation"
  72,2,"It guides to the right path, and we have believed therein, and we shall never join anything with our Lord"
  72,3,"And He, exalted be the Jadd of our Lord, has taken neither a wife nor a son"
  72,4,And that the foolish among us used to utter against Allah that which was an enormity in falsehood
  72,5,"And verily, we thought that men and Jinn would not utter a lie against Allah"
  72,6,"And verily, there were men among mankind who took shelter with the males among the Jinn, but they increased them in Rahaq"
  72,7,"And they thought as you thought, that Allah will not send any Messenger"
  72,8,And we have sought to reach the heaven; but we found it filled with stern guards and flaming fires
  72,9,"And verily, we used to sit there in stations, to (steal) a hearing, but any who listens now will find a flaming fire watching him in ambush"
  72,10,"And we know not whether evil is intended for those on the earth, or whether their Lord intends for them guidance"
  72,11,"There are among us some that are righteous, and some the contrary; we are groups having different ways"
  72,12,"And we think that we cannot escape Allah in the earth, nor can we escape Him by flight"
  72,13,"And indeed when we heard the Guidance, we believed therein, and whosoever believes in his Lord shall have no fear, either of a decrease in the reward of his good deeds or an increase in the punishment for his sins"
  72,14,"And of us some are Muslims, and of us some are Al-Qasitun. And whosoever has embraced Islam, then such have sought the right path"
  72,15,"And as for the Qasitun, they shall be firewood for Hell"
  72,16,"If they had believed in Allah, and went on the way, We would surely have bestowed on them water in abundance"
  72,17,"That We might try them thereby. And whosoever turns away from the Reminder of his Lord, He will cause him to enter in a Sa`ad torment"
  72,18,"And the Masjids are for Allah, so invoke not anyone along with Allah"
  72,19,And when the servant of Allah stood up invoking Him in prayer they just made round him a dense crowd as if sticking one over the other
  72,20,"Say: \"I invoke only my Lord, and I associate none as partners along with Him"
  72,21,"Say: \"It is not in my power to cause you harm, or to bring you to the right path"
  72,22,"Say: \"None can protect me from Allah's punishment, nor can I find refuge except in Him"
  72,23,"(Mine is) but conveyance from Allah and His Messages, and whosoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger, then verily, for him is the fire of Hell, he shall dwell therein forever"
  72,24,"Till, when they see that which they are promised, then they will know who it is that is weaker concerning helpers and less important concerning numbers"
  72,25,"Say: \"I know not whether that which you are promised is near or whether my Lord will appoint for it a distant term"
  72,26,"The All-Knower of the Unseen, and He reveals to none His Unseen"
  72,27,"Except to a Messenger whom He has chosen, and then He makes a band of watching guards to march before him and behind him"
  72,28,"Till he knows that they have conveyed the Messages of their Lord. And He surrounds all that which is with them, and He keeps count of all things"
  73,1,O you wrapped up
  73,2,"Stand (to pray) all night, except a little"
  73,3,"Half of it or less than that, a little"
  73,4,Or a little more. And Rattil the Qur'an Tartil
  73,5,"Verily, We shall send down to you a Word Thaqil"
  73,6,"Verily, rising (Nashi'ah) at night is better for understanding and more suitable for speech (recitation)"
  73,7,"Verily, for you in the day is lengthy Sabh"
  73,8,And remember the Name of your Lord and (Tabattil) devote yourself to Him with complete devotion
  73,9,"Lord of the east and the west; La ilaha illa Huwa, so take Him as a trustee"
  73,10,"And be patient with what they say, and keep away from them in a good way"
  73,11,"And leave Me alone to deal with the deniers, those who are in possession of good things of life. And give them respite for a little"
  73,12,"Verily, with Us are Ankal, and Jahim"
  73,13,"And a food that chokes, and a painful torment"
  73,14,"On the Day when the earth and the mountains will (Tarjufu) shake, and the mountains will be a heap of sand poured out"
  73,15,"Verily, We have sent to you a Messenger to be a witness over you, as We did send a Messenger to Fir`awn"
  73,16,But Fir`awn disobeyed the Messenger; so We seized him with a severe punishment
  73,17,"Then how can you protect yourselves from the punishment, if you disbelieve, on a Day that will make the children gray-headed"
  73,18,Whereon the heaven will be cleft asunder His promise is certainly to be accomplished
  73,19,"Verily, this is an admonition, therefore whosoever wills, let him take a path to His Lord"
  73,20,"Verily, your Lord knows that you do stand a little less than two-thirds of the night, or half the night, or a third of the night, and also a party of those with you. And Allah measures the night and the day. He knows that you are unable to pray the whole night, so He has turned to you. So, recite you of the Qur'an as much as may be easy for you. He knows that there will be some among you sick, others traveling through the land, seeking of Allah's bounty, yet others fighting in Allah's cause. So recite as much of the Qur'an as may be easy"
  74,1,O you enveloped in garments
  74,2,Arise and warn
  74,3,And magnify your Lord
  74,4,And purify your garments
  74,5,And keep away from Ar-Rujz
  74,6,And give not a thing in order to have more
  74,7,And be patient for the sake of your Lord
  74,8,"Then, when the Naqur is sounded"
  74,9,"Truly, that Day will be a Hard Day"
  74,10,Far from easy for the disbelievers
  74,11,Leave Me alone (to deal) with whom I created lonely
  74,12,And then granted him resources in abundance
  74,13,And children attending
  74,14,And made life smooth and comfortable for him
  74,15,After all that he desires that I should give more
  74,16,"Nay! Verily, he has been opposing Our Ayat"
  74,17,I shall force him to Sa`ud
  74,18,"Verily, he thought and plotted"
  74,19,"So let him be cursed, how he plotted"
  74,20,"And once more let him be cursed, how he plotted"
  74,21,Then he thought
  74,22,Then he frowned and he looked in a bad tempered way
  74,23,"Then he turned back, and was proud"
  74,24,"Then he said: \"This is nothing but magic from that of old"
  74,25,This is nothing but the word of a human being
  74,26,I will cast him into Saqar
  74,27,And what will make you know (exactly) what Saqar is
  74,28,"It spares not, nor does it leave (anything)"
  74,29,Scorching for the humans
  74,30,Over it are nineteen
  74,31,"And We have set none but angels as guardians of the Fire. And We have fixed their number only as a trial for the disbelievers, in order that the People of the Scripture may arrive at a certainty and that the believers may increase in faith, and that no doubt may be left for the People of the Scripture and the believers, and that those in whose hearts is a disease and the disbelievers may say: \"What does Allah intend by this example\" Thus Allah leads astray whom He wills and guides whom He wills. And none can know the hosts of your Lord but He. And this is nothing but a reminder to mankind"
  74,32,Nay! And by the moon
  74,33,And by the night when it withdraws
  74,34,And by the dawn when it brightens
  74,35,"Verily, it is but one of the greatest (signs)"
  74,36,A warning to mankind
  74,37,"To any of you that chooses to go forward, or to remain behind"
  74,38,Every person is a pledge for what he has earned
  74,39,Except those on the Right
  74,40,In Gardens they will ask one another
  74,41,About criminals (and they will say to them)
  74,42,What has caused you to enter Hell
  74,43,"They will say: \"We were not of those who used to offer the Salah"
  74,44,Nor did we feed the poor
  74,45,And we used to speak falsehood with vain speakers
  74,46,And we used to deny the Day of Recompense
  74,47,Until Al-Yaqin came to us
  74,48,So no intercession of intercessors will be of any use to them
  74,49,Then what is wrong with them that they turn away from admonition
  74,50,As if they were wild donkeys
  74,51,Fleeing from a Qaswarah
  74,52,"Nay, everyone of them desires that he should be given pages spread out"
  74,53,Nay! But they fear not the Hereafter
  74,54,"Nay, verily, this is an admonition"
  74,55,"So, whosoever wills receives admonition from it"
  74,56,"And they will not receive admonition unless Allah wills; He is the One, deserving of the Taqwa and He is the One Who forgives"
  75,1,Nay! I swear by the Day of Resurrection
  75,2,And nay! I swear by An-Nafs Al-Lawwamah
  75,3,Does man think that We shall not assemble his bones
  75,4,"Yes, We are able to put together in perfect order the tips of his fingers"
  75,5,Nay! Man desires to break out ahead of himself
  75,6,"He asks: \"When will be this Day of Resurrection"
  75,7,"So, when Bariqa the sight"
  75,8,And the moon will be eclipsed
  75,9,And the sun and moon will be joined together
  75,10,"On that Day man will say: \"Where (is the refuge) to flee"
  75,11,No! There is no refuge
  75,12,Unto your Lord will be the place of rest that Day
  75,13,"On that Day man will be informed of what he sent forward, and what he left behind"
  75,14,Nay! Man will be well informed about himself
  75,15,Though he may put forth his excuses
  75,16,Move not your tongue concerning to make haste therewith
  75,17,It is for Us to collect it and that it be recited
  75,18,"And when We have recited it to you, then follow its recitation"
  75,19,Then it is for Us to make it clear
  75,20,But no! Rather you love the present life of this world
  75,21,And neglect the Hereafter
  75,22,Some faces that Day shall be Nadirah
  75,23,Looking at their Lord
  75,24,And some faces that Day will be Basirah
  75,25,Thinking that some calamity is about to fall on them
  75,26,"Nay, when it rea- ches to the collarbones"
  75,27,"And it will be said: \"Who can cure him"
  75,28,And he will think that it was the parting
  75,29,And one shank will be joined with another shank
  75,30,The drive will be on that Day to your Lord
  75,31,"So, he neither believed nor prayed"
  75,32,"But on the contrary, he denied and turned away"
  75,33,Then he walked in conceit to his family admiring himself
  75,34,Woe to you! And then woe to you
  75,35,"Again, woe to you! And then woe to you"
  75,36,Does man think that he will be left neglected
  75,37,Was he not a Nutfah of semen emitted
  75,38,Then he became an `Alaqah; then shaped and fashioned in due proportion
  75,39,"And made of him two sexes, male and female"
  75,40,"Is it not so then, that He would be able to give life to the dead"
  76,1,"Has there not been over man a period of time, when he was not a thing worth mentioning"
  76,2,"Verily, We have created man from Nutfah Amshaj, in order to try him, so, We made him hearer and seer"
  76,3,"Verily, We guided him to the way, whether he be grateful or ungrateful"
  76,4,"Verily, We have prepared for the disbelievers iron chains, iron collars, and Sa`ir"
  76,5,"Verily, the Abrar (righteous believers) shall drink of a cup mixed with Kafur"
  76,6,"A spring wherefrom the servants of Allah will drink, causing it to gush forth abundantly"
  76,7,"They fulfill (their) vows, and they fear a Day whose evil will be wide-spreading"
  76,8,"And they give food, inspite of their love for it, to the poor, the orphan and the captive"
  76,9,"(Saying): \"We feed you seeking Allah's Face only. We wish for no reward, nor thanks from you"
  76,10,"Verily, We fear from our Lord a Day that is `Abus and Qamtarir"
  76,11,"So, Allah saved them from the evil of that Day, and gave them Nadrah (a light of beauty) and joy"
  76,12,"And their recompense shall be Paradise, and silken garments, because they were patient"
  76,13,"Reclining therein on raised couches, they will see there neither the excessive heat, nor the excessive cold"
  76,14,"And the shade thereof is close upon them, and the bunches of fruit thereof will hang low within their reach"
  76,15,And among them will be passed round vessels of silver and cups of crystal
  76,16,"(Qawarir) Crystal-clear, made of silver. They will determine the measure thereof"
  76,17,And they will be given to drink there of a cup (of wine) mixed with Zanjabil (ginger)
  76,18,"A spring there, called Salsabil"
  76,19,"And round about them will (serve) boys of everlasting youth. If you see them, you would think them scattered pearls"
  76,20,"And when you look there (in Paradise), you will see a delight (that cannot be imagined), and a great dominion"
  76,21,"Their garments will be of fine green silk, and Istabraq. They will be adorned with bracelets of silver, and their Lord will give them a purifying drink"
  76,22,"(And it will be said to them): \"Verily, this is a reward for you, and your endeavor has been accepted"
  76,23,"Verily, it is We Who have sent down the Qur'an to you by stages"
  76,24,"Therefore be patient with constancy to the command of your Lord, and obey neither a sinner nor a disbeliever among them"
  76,25,And remember the Name of your Lord every morning and afternoon
  76,26,"And during the night, prostrate yourself to Him, and glorify Him a long night through"
  76,27,"Verily, these love the present life of this world, and put behind them a heavy Day"
  76,28,"It is We Who created them, and We have made them of strong build. And when We will, We can replace them with others like them with a complete replacement"
  76,29,"Verily, this is an admonition, so whosoever wills, let him take a path to his Lord"
  76,30,"But you cannot will, unless Allah wills. Verily, Allah is Ever All-Knowing, All-Wise"
  76,31,He will admit to His mercy whom He wills and as for the wrongdoers -- He has prepared a painful torment
  77,1,By the Mursalat `Urfa
  77,2,The `Asifat `Asfa
  77,3,And the Nashirat Nashra
  77,4,The Fariqat that separate
  77,5,The Mulqiyat that remind
  77,6,Excusing or warning
  77,7,"Surely, what you are promised will occur"
  77,8,Then when the stars lose their lights
  77,9,And when Furijat the heaven
  77,10,And when the mountains are blown away
  77,11,And when the Messengers are Uqqitat
  77,12,For what Day are these signs postponed
  77,13,For the Day of Sorting Out (the men of Paradise from the men destined for Hell)
  77,14,And what will explain to you what is the Day of Sorting Out
  77,15,Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)
  77,16,Did We not destroy the ancients
  77,17,So shall We make later generations to follow them
  77,18,Thus do We deal with the criminals
  77,19,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,20,Did We not create you from a despised water
  77,21,Then We placed it in a place of safety
  77,22,For a known period
  77,23,So We did measure; and We are the best to measure
  77,24,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,25,Have We not made the earth Kifat (a receptacle)
  77,26,For the living and the dead
  77,27,"And have placed therein fixed towers, and have given you Furat water"
  77,28,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,29,"(It will be said to the disbelievers): \"Depart you to that which you used to deny"
  77,30,Depart you to a shadow in three columns
  77,31,Neither shady nor of any use against the fierce flame of the Fire
  77,32,"Verily, it (Hell) throws sparks (huge) as Al-Qasr"
  77,33,As if they were Sufr camels
  77,34,Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)
  77,35,That will be a Day when they shall not speak (during some part of it)
  77,36,And they will not be permitted to put forth any excuse
  77,37,Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)
  77,38,That will be a Day of Decision! We have brought you and the men of old together
  77,39,"So, if you have a plot, use it against Me (Allah)"
  77,40,Woe that Day to the deniers (of the Day of Resurrection)
  77,41,"Verily, those who had Taqwa, shall be amidst shades and springs"
  77,42,"And fruits, such as they desire"
  77,43,Eat and drink comfortably for that which you used to do
  77,44,"Verily, thus We reward the Muhsinin"
  77,45,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,46,"Eat and enjoy yourselves for a little while. Verily, you are criminals"
  77,47,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,48,"And when it is said to them: \"Bow down yourself!\" They bow not down"
  77,49,Woe that Day to the deniers
  77,50,Then in what statement after this will they believe
  78,1,What are they asking about
  78,2,About the great news
  78,3,About which they are in disagreement
  78,4,"Nay, they will come to know"
  78,5,"Nay, again, they will come to know"
  78,6,Have We not made the earth as a bed
  78,7,And the mountains as pegs
  78,8,And We have created you in pairs
  78,9,And We have made your sleep as a thing for rest
  78,10,And We have made the night as a covering
  78,11,And We have made the day for livelihood
  78,12,And We have built above you seven strong
  78,13,And We have made (therein) a shining lamp
  78,14,And We have sent down from the Mu`sirat water Thajjaj
  78,15,That We may produce therewith grains and vegetations
  78,16,And gardens that are Alfaf
  78,17,"Verily, the Day of Decision is a fixed time"
  78,18,"The Day when the Trumpet will be blown, and you shall come forth in crowds"
  78,19,"And the heaven shall be opened, and it will become as gates"
  78,20,And the mountains shall be moved away from their places and they will be as if they were a mirage
  78,21,"Truly, Hell is a place of ambush"
  78,22,A dwelling place for the Taghun
  78,23,They will abide therein Ahqab
  78,24,"Nothing cool shall they taste therein, nor any drink"
  78,25,"Except Hamim, and Ghassaq"
  78,26,An exact recompense (according to their evil crimes)
  78,27,"For verily, they used not to look for a reckoning"
  78,28,But they denied Our Ayat Kidhdhaba
  78,29,And all things We have recorded in a Book
  78,30,"So taste you. No increase shall We give you, except in torment"
  78,31,"Verily, for those who have Taqwa, there will be a success"
  78,32,Hada'iq and vineyards
  78,33,And Kawa`ib Atrab
  78,34,And a cup Dihaq
  78,35,"No Laghw shall they hear therein, nor lying"
  78,36,Rewarded from your Lord with a sufficient gift
  78,37,"The Lord of the heavens and the earth, and whatsoever is in between them, the Most Gracious, with Whom th- ey cannot dare to speak"
  78,38,"The Day that Ar-Ruh and the angels will stand forth in rows, they will not speak except him whom Ar-Rahman allows, and he will speak what is right"
  78,39,"That is the True Day. So, whosoever wills, let him seek a place with His Lord"
  78,40,"Verily, We have warned you of a near torment -- the Day when man will see that which his hands have sent forth, and the disbeliever will say: \"Woe to me! Would that I were dust"
  79,1,"By those who pull out, drowning"
  79,2,By those who free briskly
  79,3,"And by the swimmers, swimming"
  79,4,"And by the racers, racing"
  79,5,And by those who arrange affairs
  79,6,On the Day the Rajifah shakes
  79,7,Followed by the Radifah
  79,8,Hearts that Day will tremble
  79,9,Their vision humiliated
  79,10,"They say: \"Shall we indeed be brought back from Al-Hafirah"
  79,11,Even after we are bones Nakhirah
  79,12,"They say: \"It would in that case, be a return with loss"
  79,13,But it will be only a single Zajrah
  79,14,"When behold, they are at As-Sahirah"
  79,15,Has there come to you the story of Musa
  79,16,When his Lord called him in the holy valley of Tuwa
  79,17,"Go to Fir`awn; verily, he has transgressed all bounds"
  79,18,"And say to him: \"Would you purify yourself"
  79,19,"And that I guide you to your Lord, so you should fear Him"
  79,20,Then he showed him the great sign
  79,21,But he denied and disobeyed
  79,22,"Then he turned back, striving"
  79,23,So he gathered and called out
  79,24,"Saying: \"I am your lord, most high"
  79,25,So Allah seized him with punishing example for the Hereafter and the first (life)
  79,26,In this is a lesson for whoever fears
  79,27,Are you more difficult to create or is the heaven that He constructed
  79,28,"He raised its hei- ght, and has perfected it"
  79,29,Its night He covers and He brings out its forenoon
  79,30,And after that He spread the earth
  79,31,And brought forth therefrom its water and its pasture
  79,32,And the mountains He has fixed firmly
  79,33,As provision and benefit for you and your cattle
  79,34,But when there comes the Greatest Catastrophe
  79,35,The Day when man shall remember what he strove for
  79,36,And Hell shall be made apparent for whoever sees
  79,37,Then for him who transgressed
  79,38,And preferred the life of this world
  79,39,"Verily, his abode will be the Hell"
  79,40,"But as for him who feared standing before his Lord, and forbade himself from desire"
  79,41,"Verily, Paradise will be his abode"
  79,42,They ask you about the Hour when will be its appointed time
  79,43,What do you have to mention of it
  79,44,To your Lord it is limited
  79,45,You are only a warner for those who fear it
  79,46,The Day they see it (it will be) as if they had not tarried (in this world) except an (`Ashiyyah) afternoon or its (Duha) morning
  80,1,He frowned and turned away
  80,2,Because there came to him the blind man
  80,3,And how can you know that he might become pure
  80,4,"Or he might receive admonition, and the admonition might profit him"
  80,5,As for him who thinks himself self-sufficient
  80,6,To him you attend
  80,7,What does it matter to you if he will not become pure
  80,8,But as for him who came to you running
  80,9,And is afraid
  80,10,Of him you are neglectful and divert your attention to another
  80,11,Nay; indeed it is an admonition
  80,12,"So, whoever wills, let him pay attention to Him (it)"
  80,13,In Records held in honor
  80,14,"Exalted, purified"
  80,15,In the hands of ambassadors (Safarah)
  80,16,Honorable and obedient
  80,17,Qutila mankind! How ungrateful he is
  80,18,From what thing did He create him
  80,19,From a Nutfah He created him and then set him in due proportion
  80,20,Then He made the path easy for him
  80,21,Then He causes him to die and puts him in his grave
  80,22,"Then when it is His will, He will resurrect him"
  80,23,"Nay, but has not done what He commanded him"
  80,24,Then let man look at his food
  80,25,We pour forth water in abundance
  80,26,And We split the earth in clefts
  80,27,And We cause therein Habb to grow
  80,28,And grapes and Qadb
  80,29,And olives and date palms
  80,30,And Ghulb Hada'iq
  80,31,And fruits (Fakihah) and herbage (Abb)
  80,32,A provision and benefit for you and your cattle
  80,33,Then when there comes As-Sakhkhah
  80,34,That Day shall a man flee from his brother
  80,35,And from his mother and his father
  80,36,And from his wife and his children
  80,37,Every man that Day will have enough to make him careless of others
  80,38,Some faces that Day will be bright
  80,39,"Laughing, rejoicing at good news"
  80,40,And other faces that Day will be dust-stained
  80,41,Darkness will cover them
  80,42,"Such will be the disbelieving, the wicked evil doers"
  81,1,When the sun is Kuwwirat
  81,2,And when the stars Inkadarat
  81,3,And when the mountains are made to pass away
  81,4,And when the pregnant she-camels are neglected
  81,5,And when the wild beasts are gathered together
  81,6,And when the seas become as blazing fire
  81,7,And when the souls are joined with their mates
  81,8,And when the female infant (Al-Maw'udah) buried alive is questioned (Su'ilat)
  81,9,For what sin was she killed
  81,10,And when the pages are laid open
  81,11,And when the heaven is Kushitat
  81,12,And when Hell is Su`irat
  81,13,And when Paradise is brought near
  81,14,Every person will know what he has brought
  81,15,But nay! I swear by Al-Khunnas
  81,16,Al-Jawar Al-Kunnas
  81,17,And by the night when it `As`as
  81,18,And by the day when it Tanaffas
  81,19,"Verily, this is the Word a most honorable messenger"
  81,20,"Dhi Quwwah, with the Lord of the Throne -- Makin"
  81,21,"Obeyed there, trustworthy"
  81,22,And your companion is not a madman
  81,23,And indeed he saw him in the clear horizon
  81,24,And he withholds not a knowledge of the Unseen
  81,25,And it is not the word of the outcast Shaytan
  81,26,Then where are you going
  81,27,"Verily, this is no less than a Reminder for the creatures"
  81,28,To whomsoever among you who wills to walk straight
  81,29,And you cannot will unless that Allah wills -- the Lord of all that exists
  82,1,When the heaven is cleft asunder (Infatarat)
  82,2,And when the stars Intatharat
  82,3,And when the seas Fujjirat
  82,4,And when the graves Bu`thirat
  82,5,A person will know what he has sent forward and left behind
  82,6,"O man! What has made you careless about your Lord, the Most Generous"
  82,7,"Who created you, fashioned you perfectly, and gave you due proportion"
  82,8,"In whatever form He willed, He put you together"
  82,9,Nay! But you deny (the Day of) Ad-Din
  82,10,"But verily, over you to watch you"
  82,11,Kiraman Katibin
  82,12,They know all that you do
  82,13,"Verily, the Abrar (the righteous believers) will be in Delight"
  82,14,"And verily, the wicked will be in the blazing Fire (Hell)"
  82,15,"Therein they will enter, and taste its burning flame on the Day of Recompense"
  82,16,And they will not be absent therefrom
  82,17,And what will make you know what the Day of Recompense is
  82,18,"Again, what will make you know what the Day of Recompense is"
  82,19,"(It will be) the Day when no person shall have power for another, and the Decision, that Day, will be with Allah"
  83,1,Woe to Al-Mutaffifin
  83,2,"Those who, when they have to receive by measure from men, demand full measure"
  83,3,"And when they have to give by measure or weight to men, give less than due"
  83,4,Do they not think that they will be resurrected
  83,5,On a Great Day
  83,6,The Day when (all) mankind will stand before the Lord of all that exists
  83,7,"Nay! Truly, the Record of the wicked is in Sijjin"
  83,8,And what will make you know what Sijjin is
  83,9,A Register inscribed
  83,10,"Woe, that Day, to those who deny"
  83,11,Those who deny the Day of Recompense
  83,12,"And none can deny it except every transgressor beyond bounds, the sinner"
  83,13,"When Our Ayat are recited to him, he says: \"Tales of the ancients"
  83,14,Nay! But on their hearts is the Ran (covering) which they used to earn
  83,15,"Nay! Surely, they will be veiled from seeing their Lord that Day"
  83,16,"Then verily, they will indeed enter the burning flame of Hell"
  83,17,"Then, it will be said to them: \"This is what you used to deny"
  83,18,"Nay! Verily, the Record of Al-Abrar (the righteous believers) is (preserved) in `Illiyyin"
  83,19,And what will make you know what `Illiyyin is
  83,20,A Register inscribed
  83,21,To which bear witness those nearest
  83,22,"Verily, Al-Abrar (the righteous believers) will be in Delight"
  83,23,"On thrones, looking"
  83,24,You will recognize in their faces the brightness of delight
  83,25,They will be given to drink of pure sealed Rahiq
  83,26,"Sealed with musk, and for this let those strive who want to strive"
  83,27,It will be mixed with Tasnim
  83,28,A spring whereof drink those nearest to Allah
  83,29,"Verily, those who committed crimes used to laugh at those who believed"
  83,30,"And, whenever they passed by them, used to wink one to another"
  83,31,"And when they returned to their own people, they would return jesting"
  83,32,"And when they saw them, they said: \"Verily, these have indeed gone astray"
  83,33,But they were not sent as watchers over them
  83,34,But this Day those who believe will laugh at the disbelievers
  83,35,"On thrones, looking"
  83,36,Are not the disbelievers paid for what they used to do
  84,1,When the heaven is split asunder
  84,2,And listens to and obeys its Lord -- and it must do so
  84,3,And when the earth is stretched forth
  84,4,And has cast out all that was in it and became empty
  84,5,And listens to and obeys its Lord -- and it must do so
  84,6,"O man! Verily, you are returning towards your Lord with your deeds and actions, a sure returning, and you will meet"
  84,7,Then as for him who will be given his Record in his right hand
  84,8,He surely will receive an easy reckoning
  84,9,And will return to his family Masrur (in joy)
  84,10,But whosoever is given his Record behind his back
  84,11,He will invoke destruction
  84,12,"And he shall enter a blazing Fire, and made to taste its burning"
  84,13,"Verily, he was among his people in joy"
  84,14,"Verily, he thought that he would never return"
  84,15,"Yes! Verily, his Lord has been ever beholding him"
  84,16,But no! I swear by Ash-Shafaq
  84,17,And the night and what it Wasaqa
  84,18,And the moon when it Ittasaq
  84,19,You shall certainly travel from stage
  84,20,"What is the matter with them, that they believe not"
  84,21,"And when the Qur'an is recited to them, they fall not prostrate"
  84,22,"Nay, those who disbelieve deny"
  84,23,And Allah knows best what they gather
  84,24,"So, announce to them a painful torment"
  84,25,Save those who believe and
  85,1,By the heaven holding the Buruj
  85,2,And by by the Promised Day
  85,3,And by the Witness and by the Witnessed
  85,4,Cursed were the People of the Ditch
  85,5,Of fire fed with fuel
  85,6,When they sat by it
  85,7,And they witnessed what they were doing against the believers
  85,8,"And they had no fault except that they believed in Allah, the Almighty, Worthy of all praise"
  85,9,To Whom belongs the dominion of the heavens and the earth! And Allah is Witness over everything
  85,10,"Verily, those who put into trial the believing men and believing women, and then do not turn in repentance, then they will have the torment of Hell, and they will have the punishment of the burning Fire"
  85,11,"Verily, those who believe and do righteous good deeds, for them will be Gardens under which rivers flow. That is the supreme success"
  85,12,"Verily, the punishment of your Lord is severe and painful"
  85,13,"Verily, He it is Who begins and repeats"
  85,14,"And He is Oft-Forgiving, Al-Wadud"
  85,15,"Owner of the Throne, Al-Majid (the Glorious)"
  85,16,Doer of what He intends
  85,17,Has the story reached you of the hosts
  85,18,Of Fir`awn and Thamud
  85,19,Nay! The disbelievers (persisted) in denying
  85,20,And Allah encompasses them from behind
  85,21,Nay! This is a Glorious Qur'an
  85,22,In Al-Lawh Al-Mahfuz
  86,1,"By the heaven, and At-Tariq"
  86,2,And what will make you to know what At-Tariq is
  86,3,"The star, Ath-Thaqib"
  86,4,There is no human being but has a protector over him
  86,5,"So, let man see from what he is created"
  86,6,He is created from a water gushing forth
  86,7,Proceeding from between the backbone and the ribs
  86,8,"Verily, He is Able to bring him back"
  86,9,The Day when all the secrets will be examined
  86,10,"Then he will have no power, nor any helper"
  86,11,"By the sky which gives rain, again and again"
  86,12,And the earth which splits
  86,13,"Verily, this is the Word that separates"
  86,14,And it is not a thing for amusement
  86,15,"Verily, they are but plotting a plot"
  86,16,And I am planning a plan
  86,17,"So, give a respite to the disbelievers; deal gently with them for a while"
  87,1,"Glorify the Name of your Lord, the Most High"
  87,2,"Who has created, and then proportioned it"
  87,3,And Who has measured; and then guided
  87,4,And Who brings out the pasturage
  87,5,And then makes it dark stubble
  87,6,"We shall make you recite, so you shall not forget"
  87,7,Except what Allah may will He knows what is apparent and what is hidden
  87,8,And We shall make easy for you the easy
  87,9,Therefore remind in case the reminder profits
  87,10,The reminder will be received by him who fears
  87,11,But it will be avoided by the wretched
  87,12,Who will enter the great Fire
  87,13,There he will neither die nor live
  87,14,Indeed whosoever purifies himself shall achieve success
  87,15,"And remembers the Name of his Lord, and performs Salah"
  87,16,Rather you prefer the life of this world
  87,17,Although the Hereafter is better and more lasting
  87,18,"Verily, this is in the former Scriptures"
  87,19,The Scriptures of Ibrahim and Musa
  88,1,Has there come to you the narration of Al-Ghashiyah (the overwhelming)
  88,2,Some faces that Day will be Khashi`ah
  88,3,"Laboring, weary"
  88,4,"They will enter into Fire, Hamiyah"
  88,5,They will be given to drink from a boiling (Aniyah) spring
  88,6,No food will there be for them but from Dari
  88,7,Which will neither nourish nor avail against hunger
  88,8,Faces that Day will be joyful
  88,9,Glad with their endeavor
  88,10,In a lofty Paradise
  88,11,Where they shall neither hear harmful speech nor falsehood
  88,12,Therein will be a running spring
  88,13,Therein will be thrones raised high
  88,14,And cups set at hand
  88,15,"And Namariq, set in rows"
  88,16,"And Zarabi, spread out (Mabthuthah)"
  88,17,"Do they not look at the camels, how they are created"
  88,18,"And at the heaven, how it is raised"
  88,19,"And at the mountains, how they are rooted"
  88,20,"And at the earth, how it is outspread"
  88,21,So remind them -- you are only one who reminds
  88,22,You are not a Musaytir over them
  88,23,Save the one who turns away and disbelieves
  88,24,Then Allah will punish him with the greatest punishment
  88,25,"Verily, to Us will be their return"
  88,26,"Then verily, for Us will be their reckoning"
  89,1,By the dawn
  89,2,And by the ten nights
  89,3,And by the even and the odd
  89,4,And by the night when it departs
  89,5,Is there (not) in them sufficient proofs for men of understanding
  89,6,Saw you not how your Lord dealt with `Ad
  89,7,Iram of the pillars
  89,8,The like of which were not created in the land
  89,9,"And Thamud, who hewed out rocks in the valley"
  89,10,And Fir`awn with Al-Awtad
  89,11,Who did transgress beyond bounds in the lands
  89,12,And made therein much mischief
  89,13,"So, your Lord poured on them different kinds of severe torment"
  89,14,"Verily, your Lord is Ever Watchful"
  89,15,"As for man, when his Lord tries him by giving him honor and bounties, then he says: \"My Lord has honored me"
  89,16,"But when He tries him by straitening his means of life, he says: \"My Lord has humiliated me"
  89,17,But no! But you treat not the orphans with kindness and generosity
  89,18,And urge not one another on the feeding of the Miskin
  89,19,And you devour the Turath -- devouring with greed
  89,20,And you love wealth with love Jamma
  89,21,"Nay! When the earth is flatened, Dakkan Dakka"
  89,22,And your Lord comes with the angels in rows
  89,23,"And Hell will be brought near that Day. On that Day will man remember, but how will that remembrance avail him"
  89,24,"He will say: \"Alas! Would that I had sent forth for my life"
  89,25,So on that Day none will punish as He will punish
  89,26,And none will bind as He will bind
  89,27,O tranquil soul
  89,28,"Come back to your Lord, -- well-pleased and well-pleasing"
  89,29,Enter then among My servants
  89,30,And enter My Paradise
  90,1,Nay! I swear by this city
  90,2,And you are free in this city
  90,3,And by the begetter and that which he begot
  90,4,"Verily, We have created man in Kabad"
  90,5,Does he think that none can overcome him
  90,6,"He says: \"I have wasted wealth in abundance"
  90,7,Does he think that none sees him
  90,8,Have We not made for him two eyes
  90,9,And a tongue and two lips
  90,10,And shown him the two ways
  90,11,But he has not attempted to pass on the path that is steep
  90,12,And what will make you know the path that is steep
  90,13,Freeing a neck
  90,14,Or giving food in a day full of Masghabah
  90,15,To an orphan near of kin
  90,16,Or to a Miskin cleaving to dust
  90,17,"Then he became one of those who believed and recommended one another to patience, and recommended one another to compassion"
  90,18,They are those on the Right
  90,19,"But those who disbelieved in Our Ayat, they are those on the Left"
  90,20,Upon them Fire will Mu'sadah
  91,1,By the sun and Duhaha
  91,2,By the moon as it Talaha
  91,3,By the day as it Jallaha
  91,4,By the night as it Yaghshaha
  91,5,By the heaven and Ma Banaha
  91,6,By the earth and Ma Tahhaha
  91,7,"By Nafs, and Ma Sawwaha (Who apportioned it)"
  91,8,Then He showed it its Fujur and its Taqwa
  91,9,Indeed he succeeds who purifies it
  91,10,And indeed he fails who Dassaha
  91,11,Thamud denied through their trans- gression
  91,12,When their most wicked went forth
  91,13,"But the Messenger of Allah said to them: \"Be cautious! That is the she-camel of Allah! (Do not harm it) and (bar it not from having) its drink"
  91,14,"Then they denied him and they killed it. So their Lord destroyed them because of their sin, Fasawwaha"
  91,15,And He feared not the consequences thereof
  92,1,By the night as it envelops
  92,2,By the day as it appears
  92,3,By Him Who created male and female
  92,4,"Certainly, your efforts and deeds are diverse"
  92,5,As for him who gives and has Taqwa
  92,6,And believes in Al-Husna
  92,7,We will make smooth for him the path of ease
  92,8,But he who is greedy and thinks himself self-sufficient
  92,9,And denies Al-Husna
  92,10,We will make smooth for him the path to evil
  92,11,And what will his wealth avail him when he goes down (in destruction)
  92,12,"Truly, on Us is (to give) guidance"
  92,13,"And truly, unto Us (belong) the last (Hereafter) and the first (this world)"
  92,14,Therefore I have warned you of a Fire Talazza
  92,15,None shall enter it save the most wretched
  92,16,Who denies and turns away
  92,17,And those with Taqwa will be far removed from it
  92,18,He who gives of his wealth for self-purification
  92,19,And who has (in mind) no favor from anyone to be paid back
  92,20,"Except to seek the Face of his Lord, the Most High"
  92,21,"He, surely, will be pleased"
  93,1,By the forenoon
  93,2,By the night when it darkens
  93,3,Your Lord has neither forsaken you nor hates you
  93,4,And indeed the Hereafter is better for you than the present
  93,5,"And verily, your Lord will give you so that you shall be well-pleased"
  93,6,Did He not find you an orphan and gave you a refuge
  93,7,And He found you unaware and guided you
  93,8,And He found you poor and made you rich
  93,9,"Therefore, treat not the orphan with oppression"
  93,10,And repulse not the one who asks
  93,11,And proclaim the grace of your Lord
  94,1,Have We not opened your breast for you
  94,2,And removed from you your burden
  94,3,Which weighed down your back
  94,4,And have We not raised high your fame
  94,5,"Verily, along with every hardship is relief"
  94,6,"Verily, along with every hardship is relief"
  94,7,"So when you have finished, devote yourself to Allah's worship"
  94,8,And to your Lord turn intentions and hopes
  95,1,By At-Tin and Az-Zaytun
  95,2,By Tur Sinin
  95,3,By this city of security
  95,4,"Verily, We created man in the best form"
  95,5,Then We reduced him to the lowest of the low
  95,6,Save those who believe and do righteous deeds. Then they shall have a reward without end
  95,7,Then what causes you to deny after this the Recompense
  95,8,Is not Allah the best of judges
  96,1,Read! In the Name of your Lord Who created
  96,2,He has created man from a clot
  96,3,Read! And your Lord is the Most Generous
  96,4,Who has taught by the pen
  96,5,He has taught man that which he knew not
  96,6,"Nay! Verily, man does transgress"
  96,7,Because he considers himself self-sufficient
  96,8,"Surely, unto your Lord is the return"
  96,9,Have you seen him who prevents
  96,10,A servant when he prays
  96,11,Have you seen if he is on the guidance
  96,12,Or enjoins Taqwa
  96,13,Have you seen if he denies and turns away
  96,14,Knows he not that Allah sees
  96,15,"Nay! If he ceases not, We will scorch his forehead"
  96,16,"A lying, sinful forehead"
  96,17,Then let him call upon his council
  96,18,We will call out the guards of Hell
  96,19,Nay! Do not obey him. Fall prostrate and draw near (to Allah)
  97,1,"Verily, We have sent it down in the Night of Al-Qadr"
  97,2,And what will make you know what the Night of Al-Qadr is
  97,3,The Night of Al-Qadr is better than a thousand months
  97,4,Therein descend the angels and the Ruh by their Lord's permission with every matter
  97,5,There is peace until the appearance of dawn
  98,1,"Those who disbelieve from among the People of the Scripture and the idolators, were not going to leave until there came to them the Bayyinah"
  98,2,A Messenger from Allah reciting purified pages
  98,3,Wherein are upright Books
  98,4,And the People of the Scripture differed not until after there came to them the Bayyinah
  98,5,"And they were commanded not, but that they should worship Allah, making religion purely for Him alone, Hunafa', and that they perform Salah and give Zakah, and that is the right religion"
  98,6,"Verily, those who disbelieve from among the People of the Scripture and idolators, will abide in the fire of Hell. They are the worst of creatures"
  98,7,"Verily, those who believe and do righteous good deeds, they are the best of creatures"
  98,8,"Their reward with their Lord is Eternal Gardens, underneath which rivers flow. They will abide therein forever, Allah will be pleased with them, and they well-pleased with Him. That is for him who fears his Lord"
  99,1,When the earth quakes with its Zilzal
  99,2,And when the earth throws out its burdens
  99,3,"And man will say: \"What is the matter with it"
  99,4,That Day it will declare its information
  99,5,Because your Lord will inspire it
  99,6,That Day mankind will proceed in scattered groups that they may be shown their deeds
  99,7,"So, whosoever does good equal to the weight of a speck of dust shall see it"
  99,8,And whosoever does evil equal to the weight of a speck of dust shall see it
  100,1,"By the `Adiyat (steeds), snorting"
  100,2,Striking sparks of fire
  100,3,And scouring to the raid at dawn
  100,4,And raise the dust in clouds the while
  100,5,And penetrating forthwith as one into the midst
  100,6,"Verily, man is ungrateful to his Lord"
  100,7,And to that He bears witness
  100,8,"And verily, he is violent in the love of wealth"
  100,9,Knows he not that when the contents of the graves are poured forth
  100,10,And that which is in the breasts shall be made known
  100,11,"Verily, that Day their Lord will be Well-Acquainted with them"
  101,1,Al-Qari`ah
  101,2,What is Al-Qari`ah
  101,3,And what will make you know what Al-Qari`ah is
  101,4,It is a Day whereon mankind will be like moths scattered about
  101,5,"And the mountains will be like wool, carded"
  101,6,Then as for him whose Balance will be heavy
  101,7,He will live a pleasant life
  101,8,But as for him whose Balance will be light
  101,9,His mother will be Hawiyah
  101,10,And what will make you know what it is
  101,11,A fire Hamiyah
  102,1,The mutual increase diverts you
  102,2,Until you visit the graves
  102,3,Nay! You shall come to know
  102,4,Again nay! You shall come to know
  102,5,Nay! If you knew with a sure knowledge
  102,6,"Verily, you shall see the blazing Fire"
  102,7,"And again, you shall see it with certainty of sight"
  102,8,Then on that Day you shall be asked about the delights
  103,1,By Al-`Asr
  103,2,"Verily, man is in loss"
  103,3,"Except those who believe and do righteous deeds, and recommend one another to the truth, and recommend one another to patience"
  104,1,Woe to every Humazah Lumazah
  104,2,Who has gathered wealth and counted it
  104,3,He thinks that his wealth will make him last forever
  104,4,"But no! Verily, he will be thrown into Al-Hutamah"
  104,5,And what will make you know what Al-Hutamah is
  104,6,"The fire of Allah, Al-Muqadah"
  104,7,Which leaps up over the hearts
  104,8,"Verily, it shall Mu'sadah upon them"
  104,9,In pillars stretched forth
  105,1,Have you not seen how your Lord dealt with the Owners of the Elephant
  105,2,Did He not make their plot go astray
  105,3,"And He sent against them birds, in flocks (Ababil)"
  105,4,Striking them with stones of Sijjil
  105,5,"And He made them like `Asf, Ma'kul"
  106,1,For the Ilaf of the Quraysh
  106,2,"Their Ilaf caravans, in winter and in summer"
  106,3,"So, let them worship the Lord of this House"
  106,4,"Who has fed them against hunger, and has made them safe from fear"
  107,1,Have you seen him who denies Ad-Din
  107,2,That is he who repulses the orphan
  107,3,And urges not the feeding of Al-Miskin
  107,4,"So, woe unto those performers of Salah"
  107,5,Those who with their Salah are Sahun
  107,6,Those who do good deeds only to be seen
  107,7,And withhold Al-Ma`un
  108,1,"Verily, We have granted you Al-Kawthar"
  108,2,Therefore turn in prayer to your Lord and sacrifice
  108,3,"For he who hates you, he will be cut off"
  109,1,"Say: \"O disbelievers"
  109,2,I worship not that which you worship
  109,3,Nor will you worship whom I worship
  109,4,And I shall not worship that which you are worshipping
  109,5,Nor will you worship that which I worship
  109,6,"To you be your religion, and to me my religion"
  110,1,When there comes the help of Allah and the Conquest
  110,2,And you see that the people enter Allah's religion in crowds
  110,3,"So, glorify the praises of your Lord, and ask His forgiveness. Verily, He is the One Who accepts the repentance and Who forgives"
  111,1,Perish the two hands of Abu Lahab and perish he
  111,2,His wealth and his children will not benefit him
  111,3,He will enter a Fire full of flames
  111,4,"And his wife too, who carries wood"
  111,5,In her neck is a twisted rope of Masad
  112,1,"Say: \"He is Allah, One"
  112,2,Allah As-Samad
  112,3,"He begets not, nor was He begotten"
  112,4,And there is none comparable to Him
  113,1,"Say: \"I seek refuge with the Lord of Al-Falaq"
  113,2,From the evil of what He has created
  113,3,And from the evil of the Ghasiq when Waqab
  113,4,And from the evil of the blowers in knots
  113,5,And from the evil of the envier when he envies
  114,1,"Say: \"I seek refuge with the Lord of An-Nas"
  114,2,The King of An-Nas
  114,3,The God of An-Nas
  114,4,From the evil of the whisperer who withdraws
  114,5,Who whispers in the breasts of An-Nas
  114,6,Of Jinn and An-Nas